91CanvasCompositingStrategy canvasCompositingStrategy(const RenderObject& renderer)
92{
93 ASSERT(renderer.isCanvas());
94
95 const HTMLCanvasElement* canvas = downcast<HTMLCanvasElement>(renderer.node());
96 auto* context = canvas->renderingContext();
97 if (!context || !context->isAccelerated())
98 return UnacceleratedCanvas;
99
100 if (context->isGPUBased())
101 return CanvasAsLayerContents;
102
103 return CanvasPaintedToLayer; // On Mac and iOS we paint accelerated canvases into their layers.
104}

106// This acts as a cache of what we know about what is painting into this RenderLayerBacking.
107class PaintedContentsInfo {
108public:
109 enum class ContentsTypeDetermination {
110 Unknown,
111 SimpleContainer,
112 DirectlyCompositedImage,
113 Painted
114 };
115
116 PaintedContentsInfo(RenderLayerBacking& inBacking)
117 : m_backing(inBacking)
118 {
119 }
120
121 void setWantsSubpixelAntialiasedTextState(bool wantsSubpixelAntialiasedTextState)
122 {
123 m_subpixelAntialiasedText = wantsSubpixelAntialiasedTextState ? RequestState::Unknown : RequestState::DontCare;
124 }
125
126 RequestState paintsBoxDecorationsDetermination();
127 bool paintsBoxDecorations()
128 {
129 RequestState state = paintsBoxDecorationsDetermination();
130 return state == RequestState::True || state == RequestState::Undetermined;
131 }
132
133 RequestState paintsContentDetermination();
134 bool paintsContent()
135 {
136 RequestState state = paintsContentDetermination();
137 return state == RequestState::True || state == RequestState::Undetermined;
138 }
139
140 RequestState paintsSubpixelAntialiasedTextDetermination();
141 bool paintsSubpixelAntialiasedText()
142 {
143 RequestState state = paintsSubpixelAntialiasedTextDetermination();
144 return state == RequestState::True || state == RequestState::Undetermined;
145 }
146
147 ContentsTypeDetermination contentsTypeDetermination();
148 bool isSimpleContainer()
149 {
150 return contentsTypeDetermination() == ContentsTypeDetermination::SimpleContainer;
151 }
152
153 bool isDirectlyCompositedImage()
154 {
155 return contentsTypeDetermination() == ContentsTypeDetermination::DirectlyCompositedImage;
156 }
157
158 RenderLayerBacking& m_backing;
159 RequestState m_boxDecorations { RequestState::Unknown };
160 RequestState m_content { RequestState::Unknown };
161 RequestState m_subpixelAntialiasedText { RequestState::DontCare };
162
163 ContentsTypeDetermination m_contentsType { ContentsTypeDetermination::Unknown };
164};
165
166RequestState PaintedContentsInfo::paintsBoxDecorationsDetermination()
167{
168 if (m_boxDecorations != RequestState::Unknown)
169 return m_boxDecorations;
170
171 m_boxDecorations = m_backing.paintsBoxDecorations() ? RequestState::True : RequestState::False;
172 return m_boxDecorations;
173}
174
175RequestState PaintedContentsInfo::paintsContentDetermination()
176{
177 if (m_content != RequestState::Unknown && m_subpixelAntialiasedText != RequestState::Unknown)
178 return m_content;
179
180 RenderLayer::PaintedContentRequest contentRequest;
181 if (m_subpixelAntialiasedText == RequestState::Unknown)
182 contentRequest.hasSubpixelAntialiasedText = RequestState::Unknown;
183
184 m_content = m_backing.paintsContent(contentRequest) ? RequestState::True : RequestState::False;
185
186 if (m_subpixelAntialiasedText == RequestState::Unknown)
187 m_subpixelAntialiasedText = contentRequest.hasSubpixelAntialiasedText;
188
189 return m_content;
190}
191
192RequestState PaintedContentsInfo::paintsSubpixelAntialiasedTextDetermination()
193{
194 if (m_subpixelAntialiasedText != RequestState::Unknown)
195 return m_subpixelAntialiasedText;
196
197 paintsContentDetermination();
198
199 return m_subpixelAntialiasedText;
200}
201
202PaintedContentsInfo::ContentsTypeDetermination PaintedContentsInfo::contentsTypeDetermination()
203{
204 if (m_contentsType != ContentsTypeDetermination::Unknown)
205 return m_contentsType;
206
207 if (m_backing.isSimpleContainerCompositingLayer(*this))
208 m_contentsType = ContentsTypeDetermination::SimpleContainer;
209 else if (m_backing.isDirectlyCompositedImage())
210 m_contentsType = ContentsTypeDetermination::DirectlyCompositedImage;
211 else
212 m_contentsType = ContentsTypeDetermination::Painted;
213
214 return m_contentsType;
215}

218RenderLayerBacking::RenderLayerBacking(RenderLayer& layer)
219 : m_owningLayer(layer)
220{
221 if (layer.isRenderViewLayer()) {
222 m_isMainFrameRenderViewLayer = renderer().frame().isMainFrame();
223 m_isFrameLayerWithTiledBacking = renderer().page().chrome().client().shouldUseTiledBackingForFrameView(renderer().view().frameView());
224 }
225
226 createPrimaryGraphicsLayer();
227#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
228 setRequiresBackgroundLayer(layer.renderer().isRenderFullScreen());
229#endif
230
231 if (auto* tiledBacking = this->tiledBacking()) {
232 tiledBacking->setIsInWindow(renderer().page().isInWindow());
233
234 if (m_isFrameLayerWithTiledBacking) {
235 tiledBacking->setScrollingPerformanceTestingEnabled(renderer().settings().scrollingPerformanceTestingEnabled());
236 adjustTiledBackingCoverage();
237 }
238 }
239}

241RenderLayerBacking::~RenderLayerBacking()
242{
243#if USE(OWNING_LAYER_BEAR_TRAP)
244 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_owningLayerBearTrap == BEAR_TRAP_VALUE, "~RenderLayerBacking: m_owningLayerBearTrap caught the bear (55699292)");
245 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(&m_owningLayer, "~RenderLayerBacking: m_owningLayer is null (55699292)");
246#endif
247 // Note that m_owningLayer->backing() is null here.
248 updateAncestorClipping(false, nullptr);
249 updateChildClippingStrategy(false);
250 updateDescendantClippingLayer(false);
251 updateOverflowControlsLayers(false, false, false);
252 updateForegroundLayer(false);
253 updateBackgroundLayer(false);
254 updateMaskingLayer(false, false);
255 updateScrollingLayers(false);
256
257 ASSERT(!m_viewportConstrainedNodeID);
258 ASSERT(!m_scrollingNodeID);
259 ASSERT(!m_frameHostingNodeID);
260 ASSERT(!m_positioningNodeID);
261
262 destroyGraphicsLayers();
263}

265void RenderLayerBacking::willBeDestroyed()
266{
267#if USE(OWNING_LAYER_BEAR_TRAP)
268 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_owningLayerBearTrap == BEAR_TRAP_VALUE, "RenderLayerBacking::willBeDestroyed(): m_owningLayerBearTrap caught the bear (55699292)");
269 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(&m_owningLayer, "RenderLayerBacking::willBeDestroyed(): m_owningLayer is null (55699292)");
270#endif
271
272 ASSERT(m_owningLayer.backing() == this);
273 compositor().removeFromScrollCoordinatedLayers(m_owningLayer);
274
275 clearBackingSharingLayers();
276}

280 if (layer && layer->type() == GraphicsLayer::Type::Normal && layer->tiledBacking())
281 compositor().layerTiledBackingUsageChanged(layer, false);
282}

284static void clearBackingSharingLayerProviders(Vector<WeakPtr<RenderLayer>>& sharingLayers, const RenderLayer& providerLayer)
285{
286 for (auto& layerWeakPtr : sharingLayers) {
287 if (!layerWeakPtr)
288 continue;
289 if (layerWeakPtr->backingProviderLayer() == &providerLayer)
290 layerWeakPtr->setBackingProviderLayer(nullptr);
291 }
292}
293
294void RenderLayerBacking::setBackingSharingLayers(Vector<WeakPtr<RenderLayer>>&& sharingLayers)
295{
296 bool sharingLayersChanged = m_backingSharingLayers != sharingLayers;
297 if (sharingLayersChanged) {
298 // For layers that used to share and no longer do, and are not composited, recompute repaint rects.
299 for (auto& oldSharingLayer : m_backingSharingLayers) {
300 // Layers that go from shared to composited have their repaint rects recomputed in RenderLayerCompositor::updateBacking().
301 // FIXME: Two O(n^2) traversals in this funtion. Probably OK because sharing lists are usually small, but still.
302 if (!sharingLayers.contains(oldSharingLayer) && !oldSharingLayer->isComposited())
303 oldSharingLayer->computeRepaintRectsIncludingDescendants();
304 }
305 }
306
307 clearBackingSharingLayerProviders(m_backingSharingLayers, m_owningLayer);
308
309 if (sharingLayers != m_backingSharingLayers) {
310 if (sharingLayers.size())
311 setRequiresOwnBackingStore(true);
312 setContentsNeedDisplay(); // This could be optimized to only repaint rects for changed layers.
313 }
314
315 auto oldSharingLayers = WTFMove(m_backingSharingLayers);
316 m_backingSharingLayers = WTFMove(sharingLayers);
317
318 for (auto& layerWeakPtr : m_backingSharingLayers)
319 layerWeakPtr->setBackingProviderLayer(&m_owningLayer);
320
321 if (sharingLayersChanged) {
322 // For layers that are newly sharing, recompute repaint rects.
323 for (auto& currentSharingLayer : m_backingSharingLayers) {
324 if (!oldSharingLayers.contains(currentSharingLayer))
325 currentSharingLayer->computeRepaintRectsIncludingDescendants();
326 }
327 }
328}
329
330void RenderLayerBacking::removeBackingSharingLayer(RenderLayer& layer)
331{
332 layer.setBackingProviderLayer(nullptr);
333 m_backingSharingLayers.removeAll(&layer);
334}
335
336void RenderLayerBacking::clearBackingSharingLayers()
337{
338 clearBackingSharingLayerProviders(m_backingSharingLayers, m_owningLayer);
339 m_backingSharingLayers.clear();
340}

342Ref<GraphicsLayer> RenderLayerBacking::createGraphicsLayer(const String& name, GraphicsLayer::Type layerType)
343{
344 auto* graphicsLayerFactory = renderer().page().chrome().client().graphicsLayerFactory();
345
346 auto graphicsLayer = GraphicsLayer::create(graphicsLayerFactory, *this, layerType);
347
348 graphicsLayer->setName(name);
349
350#if PLATFORM(COCOA) && USE(CA)
351 graphicsLayer->setAcceleratesDrawing(compositor().acceleratedDrawingEnabled());
352 graphicsLayer->setUsesDisplayListDrawing(compositor().displayListDrawingEnabled());
353#endif
354
355 return graphicsLayer;
356}

394static TiledBacking::TileCoverage computePageTiledBackingCoverage(const RenderLayer& layer)
395{
396 // If the page is non-visible, don't incur the cost of keeping extra tiles for scrolling.
397 if (!layer.page().isVisible())
398 return TiledBacking::CoverageForVisibleArea;
399
400 auto& frameView = layer.renderer().view().frameView();
401
402 TiledBacking::TileCoverage tileCoverage = TiledBacking::CoverageForVisibleArea;
403 bool useMinimalTilesDuringLiveResize = frameView.inLiveResize();
404 if (frameView.speculativeTilingEnabled() && !useMinimalTilesDuringLiveResize) {
405 bool clipsToExposedRect = static_cast<bool>(frameView.viewExposedRect());
406 if (frameView.horizontalScrollbarMode() != ScrollbarAlwaysOff || clipsToExposedRect)
407 tileCoverage |= TiledBacking::CoverageForHorizontalScrolling;
408
409 if (frameView.verticalScrollbarMode() != ScrollbarAlwaysOff || clipsToExposedRect)
410 tileCoverage |= TiledBacking::CoverageForVerticalScrolling;
411 }
412 return tileCoverage;
413}
414
415static TiledBacking::TileCoverage computeOverflowTiledBackingCoverage(const RenderLayer& layer)
416{
417 // If the page is non-visible, don't incur the cost of keeping extra tiles for scrolling.
418 if (!layer.page().isVisible())
419 return TiledBacking::CoverageForVisibleArea;
420
421 auto& frameView = layer.renderer().view().frameView();
422
423 TiledBacking::TileCoverage tileCoverage = TiledBacking::CoverageForVisibleArea;
424 bool useMinimalTilesDuringLiveResize = frameView.inLiveResize();
425 if (!useMinimalTilesDuringLiveResize) {
426 if (auto* scrollableArea = layer.scrollableArea()) {
427 if (scrollableArea->hasScrollableHorizontalOverflow())
428 tileCoverage |= TiledBacking::CoverageForHorizontalScrolling;
429
430 if (scrollableArea->hasScrollableVerticalOverflow())
431 tileCoverage |= TiledBacking::CoverageForVerticalScrolling;
432 }
433 }
434 return tileCoverage;
435}
436
437void RenderLayerBacking::adjustTiledBackingCoverage()
438{
439 if (m_isFrameLayerWithTiledBacking) {
440 auto tileCoverage = computePageTiledBackingCoverage(m_owningLayer);
441 if (auto* tiledBacking = this->tiledBacking())
442 tiledBacking->setTileCoverage(tileCoverage);
443 }
444
445 if (m_owningLayer.hasCompositedScrollableOverflow() && m_scrolledContentsLayer) {
446 if (auto* tiledBacking = m_scrolledContentsLayer->tiledBacking()) {
447 auto tileCoverage = computeOverflowTiledBackingCoverage(m_owningLayer);
448 tiledBacking->setTileCoverage(tileCoverage);
449 }
450 }
451}

513void RenderLayerBacking::createPrimaryGraphicsLayer()
514{
515 String layerName = m_owningLayer.name();
516 const unsigned maxLayerNameLength = 100;
517 if (layerName.length() > maxLayerNameLength) {
518 layerName.truncate(maxLayerNameLength);
519 layerName.append("...");
520 }
521 m_graphicsLayer = createGraphicsLayer(layerName, m_isFrameLayerWithTiledBacking ? GraphicsLayer::Type::PageTiledBacking : GraphicsLayer::Type::Normal);
522
523 if (m_isFrameLayerWithTiledBacking) {
524 m_childContainmentLayer = createGraphicsLayer("Page TiledBacking containment");
525 m_graphicsLayer->addChild(*m_childContainmentLayer);
526 }
527
528#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
529 if (m_isMainFrameRenderViewLayer) {
530 // Page scale is applied above the RenderView on iOS.
531 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsOpaque(!compositor().viewHasTransparentBackground());
532 m_graphicsLayer->setAppliesPageScale();
533 }
534#endif
535
536#if PLATFORM(COCOA) && USE(CA)
537 if (!compositor().acceleratedDrawingEnabled() && renderer().isCanvas()) {
538 const HTMLCanvasElement* canvas = downcast<HTMLCanvasElement>(renderer().element());
539 if (canvas->shouldAccelerate(canvas->size()))
540 m_graphicsLayer->setAcceleratesDrawing(true);
541 }
542#endif
543
544 updateOpacity(renderer().style());
545 updateTransform(renderer().style());
546 updateFilters(renderer().style());
547#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
548 updateBackdropFilters(renderer().style());
549#endif
550#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
551 updateBlendMode(renderer().style());
552#endif
553 updateCustomAppearance(renderer().style());
554}
555
556#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
557void RenderLayerBacking::layerWillBeDestroyed()
558{
559 auto& renderer = this->renderer();
560 if (is<RenderEmbeddedObject>(renderer) && downcast<RenderEmbeddedObject>(renderer).allowsAcceleratedCompositing()) {
561 auto* pluginViewBase = downcast<PluginViewBase>(downcast<RenderWidget>(renderer).widget());
562 if (pluginViewBase && m_graphicsLayer->contentsLayerForMedia())
563 pluginViewBase->detachPluginLayer();
564 }
565}

567bool RenderLayerBacking::needsIOSDumpRenderTreeMainFrameRenderViewLayerIsAlwaysOpaqueHack(const GraphicsLayer& layer) const
568{
569 if (m_isMainFrameRenderViewLayer && IOSApplication::isDumpRenderTree()) {
570 // In iOS WebKit1 the main frame's RenderView layer is always transparent. We lie that it is opaque so that
571 // internals.layerTreeAsText() tests succeed.
572 ASSERT_UNUSED(layer, !layer.contentsOpaque());
573 return true;
574 }
575 return false;
576}
577#endif

579void RenderLayerBacking::destroyGraphicsLayers()
580{
581 if (m_graphicsLayer) {
582 m_graphicsLayer->setMaskLayer(nullptr);
583 m_graphicsLayer->setReplicatedByLayer(nullptr);
584 willDestroyLayer(m_graphicsLayer.get());
585 }
586
587 GraphicsLayer::clear(m_maskLayer);
588
589 if (m_ancestorClippingStack)
590 removeClippingStackLayers(*m_ancestorClippingStack);
591
592 if (m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack)
593 removeClippingStackLayers(*m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack);
594
595 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(m_contentsContainmentLayer);
596 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(m_foregroundLayer);
597 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(m_backgroundLayer);
598 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(m_childContainmentLayer);
599 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(m_childClippingMaskLayer);
600 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(m_scrollContainerLayer);
601 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(m_scrolledContentsLayer);
602 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(m_graphicsLayer);
603}

609
610static LayoutRect clippingLayerBox(const RenderBox& renderBox)
611{
612 LayoutRect result = LayoutRect::infiniteRect();
613 if (renderBox.hasOverflowClip())
614 result = renderBox.overflowClipRect({ }, 0); // FIXME: Incorrect for CSS regions.
615
616 if (renderBox.hasClip())
617 result.intersect(renderBox.clipRect({ }, 0)); // FIXME: Incorrect for CSS regions.
618
619 return result;
620}

622static LayoutRect overflowControlsHostLayerRect(const RenderBox& renderBox)
623{
624 return renderBox.paddingBoxRectIncludingScrollbar();
625}

631
632void RenderLayerBacking::updateTransform(const RenderStyle& style)
633{
634 // FIXME: This could use m_owningLayer.transform(), but that currently has transform-origin
635 // baked into it, and we don't want that.
636 TransformationMatrix t;
637 if (m_owningLayer.hasTransform()) {
638 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer());
639 style.applyTransform(t, snapRectToDevicePixels(renderBox.borderBoxRect(), deviceScaleFactor()), RenderStyle::individualTransformOperations);
640 makeMatrixRenderable(t, compositor().canRender3DTransforms());
641 }
642
643 if (m_contentsContainmentLayer) {
644 m_contentsContainmentLayer->setTransform(t);
645 m_graphicsLayer->setTransform({ });
646 } else
647 m_graphicsLayer->setTransform(t);
648}
649
650void RenderLayerBacking::updateChildrenTransformAndAnchorPoint(const LayoutRect& primaryGraphicsLayerRect, LayoutSize offsetFromParentGraphicsLayer)
651{
652 if (!renderer().hasTransformRelatedProperty()) {
653 auto defaultAnchorPoint = FloatPoint3D { 0.5, 0.5, 0 };
654 m_graphicsLayer->setAnchorPoint(defaultAnchorPoint);
655 if (m_contentsContainmentLayer)
656 m_contentsContainmentLayer->setAnchorPoint(defaultAnchorPoint);
657
658 if (m_scrolledContentsLayer)
659 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setPreserves3D(false);
660 return;
661 }
662
663 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer());
664 const auto deviceScaleFactor = this->deviceScaleFactor();
665 auto borderBoxRect = renderBox.borderBoxRect();
666 auto transformOrigin = computeTransformOriginForPainting(borderBoxRect);
667 auto layerOffset = roundPointToDevicePixels(toLayoutPoint(offsetFromParentGraphicsLayer), deviceScaleFactor);
668 auto anchor = FloatPoint3D {
669 primaryGraphicsLayerRect.width() ? ((layerOffset.x() - primaryGraphicsLayerRect.x()) + transformOrigin.x()) / primaryGraphicsLayerRect.width() : 0.5f,
670 primaryGraphicsLayerRect.height() ? ((layerOffset.y() - primaryGraphicsLayerRect.y())+ transformOrigin.y()) / primaryGraphicsLayerRect.height() : 0.5f,
671 transformOrigin.z()
672 };
673
674 if (m_contentsContainmentLayer)
675 m_contentsContainmentLayer->setAnchorPoint(anchor);
676 else
677 m_graphicsLayer->setAnchorPoint(anchor);
678
679 auto removeChildrenTransformFromLayers = [&](GraphicsLayer* layerToIgnore = nullptr) {
680 auto* clippingLayer = this->clippingLayer();
681 if (clippingLayer && clippingLayer != layerToIgnore)
682 clippingLayer->setChildrenTransform({ });
683
684 if (m_scrollContainerLayer && m_scrollContainerLayer != layerToIgnore) {
685 m_scrollContainerLayer->setChildrenTransform({ });
686 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setPreserves3D(false);
687 }
688
689 if (m_graphicsLayer != layerToIgnore)
690 m_graphicsLayer->setChildrenTransform({ });
691 };
692
693 if (!renderer().style().hasPerspective()) {
694 removeChildrenTransformFromLayers();
695 return;
696 }
697
698 auto layerForChildrenTransform = [&] {
699 if (m_scrollContainerLayer)
700 return std::make_tuple(m_scrollContainerLayer.get(), scrollContainerLayerBox(renderBox));
701
702 if (auto* layer = clippingLayer())
703 return std::make_tuple(layer, clippingLayerBox(renderBox));
704
705 return std::make_tuple(m_graphicsLayer.get(), borderBoxRect);
706 };
707
708 auto [layerForPerspective, perspectiveRelativeBox] = layerForChildrenTransform();
709 // FIXME: perspectiveRelativeBox isn't quite right here. This needs work: webkit.org/b/211787.
710 auto perspectiveTransform = owningLayer().perspectiveTransform(perspectiveRelativeBox);
711
712 // If we have scrolling layers, we need the children transform on m_scrollContainerLayer to
713 // affect children of m_scrolledContentsLayer, so set setPreserves3D(true).
714 if (layerForPerspective == m_scrollContainerLayer)
715 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setPreserves3D(true);
716
717 layerForPerspective->setChildrenTransform(perspectiveTransform);
718 removeChildrenTransformFromLayers(layerForPerspective);
719}

792bool RenderLayerBacking::shouldClipCompositedBounds() const
793{
794#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
795 // Scrollbar layers use this layer for relative positioning, so don't clip.
796 if (layerForHorizontalScrollbar() || layerForVerticalScrollbar())
797 return false;
798#endif
799
800 if (m_isFrameLayerWithTiledBacking)
801 return false;
802
803 if (layerOrAncestorIsTransformedOrUsingCompositedScrolling(m_owningLayer))
804 return false;
805
806 return true;

809static bool hasNonZeroTransformOrigin(const RenderObject& renderer)
810{
811 const RenderStyle& style = renderer.style();
812 return (style.transformOriginX().isFixed() && style.transformOriginX().value())
813 || (style.transformOriginY().isFixed() && style.transformOriginY().value());
814}
815
816bool RenderLayerBacking::updateCompositedBounds()
817{
818#if USE(OWNING_LAYER_BEAR_TRAP)
819 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_owningLayerBearTrap == BEAR_TRAP_VALUE, "RenderLayerBacking::updateCompositedBounds(): m_owningLayerBearTrap caught the bear (55699292)");
820 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(&m_owningLayer, "RenderLayerBacking::updateCompositedBounds(): m_owningLayer is null (55699292)");
821#endif
822
823 LayoutRect layerBounds = m_owningLayer.calculateLayerBounds(&m_owningLayer, { }, RenderLayer::defaultCalculateLayerBoundsFlags() | RenderLayer::ExcludeHiddenDescendants | RenderLayer::DontConstrainForMask);
824 // Clip to the size of the document or enclosing overflow-scroll layer.
825 // If this or an ancestor is transformed, we can't currently compute the correct rect to intersect with.
826 // We'd need RenderObject::convertContainerToLocalQuad(), which doesn't yet exist.
827 if (shouldClipCompositedBounds()) {
828 auto& view = renderer().view();
829 auto* rootLayer = view.layer();
830
831 LayoutRect clippingBounds;
832 if (renderer().isFixedPositioned() && renderer().container() == &view)
833 clippingBounds = view.frameView().rectForFixedPositionLayout();
834 else
835 clippingBounds = view.unscaledDocumentRect();
836
837 if (&m_owningLayer != rootLayer)
838 clippingBounds.intersect(m_owningLayer.backgroundClipRect(RenderLayer::ClipRectsContext(rootLayer, AbsoluteClipRects)).rect()); // FIXME: Incorrect for CSS regions.
839
840 LayoutPoint delta = m_owningLayer.convertToLayerCoords(rootLayer, LayoutPoint(), RenderLayer::AdjustForColumns);
841 clippingBounds.move(-delta.x(), -delta.y());
842
843 layerBounds.intersect(clippingBounds);
844 }
845
846 // If the backing provider has overflow:clip, we know all sharing layers are affected by the clip because they are containing-block descendants.
847 if (!renderer().hasOverflowClip()) {
848 for (auto& layerWeakPtr : m_backingSharingLayers) {
849 auto* boundsRootLayer = &m_owningLayer;
850 ASSERT(layerWeakPtr->isDescendantOf(m_owningLayer));
851 auto offset = layerWeakPtr->offsetFromAncestor(&m_owningLayer);
852 auto bounds = layerWeakPtr->calculateLayerBounds(boundsRootLayer, offset, RenderLayer::defaultCalculateLayerBoundsFlags() | RenderLayer::ExcludeHiddenDescendants | RenderLayer::DontConstrainForMask);
853 layerBounds.unite(bounds);
854 }
855 }
856
857 // If the element has a transform-origin that has fixed lengths, and the renderer has zero size,
858 // then we need to ensure that the compositing layer has non-zero size so that we can apply
859 // the transform-origin via the GraphicsLayer anchorPoint (which is expressed as a fractional value).
860 if (layerBounds.isEmpty() && (hasNonZeroTransformOrigin(renderer()) || renderer().style().hasPerspective())) {
861 layerBounds.setWidth(1);
862 layerBounds.setHeight(1);
863 m_artificiallyInflatedBounds = true;
864 } else
865 m_artificiallyInflatedBounds = false;
866
867 return setCompositedBounds(layerBounds);
868}
869
870void RenderLayerBacking::updateAllowsBackingStoreDetaching(const LayoutRect& absoluteBounds)
871{
872 auto setAllowsBackingStoreDetaching = [&](bool allowDetaching) {
873 m_graphicsLayer->setAllowsBackingStoreDetaching(allowDetaching);
874 if (m_foregroundLayer)
875 m_foregroundLayer->setAllowsBackingStoreDetaching(allowDetaching);
876 if (m_backgroundLayer)
877 m_backgroundLayer->setAllowsBackingStoreDetaching(allowDetaching);
878 if (m_scrolledContentsLayer)
879 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setAllowsBackingStoreDetaching(allowDetaching);
880 };
881
882 if (!m_owningLayer.behavesAsFixed()) {
883 setAllowsBackingStoreDetaching(true);
884 return;
885 }
886
887 // We'll allow detaching if the layer is outside the layout viewport. Fixed layers inside
888 // the layout viewport can be revealed by async scrolling, so we want to pin their backing store.
889 FrameView& frameView = renderer().view().frameView();
890 LayoutRect fixedLayoutRect;
891 if (frameView.useFixedLayout())
892 fixedLayoutRect = renderer().view().unscaledDocumentRect();
893 else
894 fixedLayoutRect = frameView.rectForFixedPositionLayout();
895
896 bool allowDetaching = !fixedLayoutRect.intersects(absoluteBounds);
897 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "RenderLayerBacking (layer " << &m_owningLayer << ") updateAllowsBackingStoreDetaching - absoluteBounds " << absoluteBounds << " layoutViewportRect " << fixedLayoutRect << ", allowDetaching " << allowDetaching);
898 setAllowsBackingStoreDetaching(allowDetaching);
899}

905

907 innerCompositor->frameViewDidChangeSize();
908 innerCompositor->frameViewDidChangeLocation(flooredIntPoint(contentsBox().location()));

912void RenderLayerBacking::updateAfterLayout(bool needsClippingUpdate, bool needsFullRepaint)
913{
914#if USE(OWNING_LAYER_BEAR_TRAP)
915 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_owningLayerBearTrap == BEAR_TRAP_VALUE, "RenderLayerBacking::updateAfterLayout(): m_owningLayerBearTrap caught the bear (55699292)");
916 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(&m_owningLayer, "RenderLayerBacking::updateAfterLayout(): m_owningLayer is null (55699292)");
917#endif
918
919 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "RenderLayerBacking::updateAfterLayout (layer " << &m_owningLayer << " needsClippingUpdate " << needsClippingUpdate << " needsFullRepaint " << needsFullRepaint);
920
921 // This is the main trigger for layout changing layer geometry, but we have to do the work again in updateBackingAndHierarchy()
922 // when we know the final compositing hierarchy. We can't just set dirty bits from RenderLayer::setSize() because that doesn't
923 // take overflow into account.
924 if (updateCompositedBounds()) {
925 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingGeometryUpdate();
926 // This layer's geometry affects those of its children.
927 m_owningLayer.setChildrenNeedCompositingGeometryUpdate();
928 } else if (needsClippingUpdate) {
929 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingConfigurationUpdate();
930 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingGeometryUpdate();
931 }
932
933 if (needsFullRepaint && canIssueSetNeedsDisplay())
934 setContentsNeedDisplay();
935}

937// This can only update things that don't require up-to-date layout.
938void RenderLayerBacking::updateConfigurationAfterStyleChange()
939{
940 updateMaskingLayer(renderer().hasMask(), renderer().hasClipPath());
941
942 if (m_owningLayer.hasReflection()) {
943 if (m_owningLayer.reflectionLayer()->backing()) {
944 auto* reflectionLayer = m_owningLayer.reflectionLayer()->backing()->graphicsLayer();
945 m_graphicsLayer->setReplicatedByLayer(reflectionLayer);
946 }
947 } else
948 m_graphicsLayer->setReplicatedByLayer(nullptr);
949
950 // FIXME: do we care if opacity is animating?
951 auto& style = renderer().style();
952 updateOpacity(style);
953 updateFilters(style);
954
955#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
956 updateBackdropFilters(style);
957#endif
958#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
959 updateBlendMode(style);
960#endif
961 updateCustomAppearance(style);
962}
963
964bool RenderLayerBacking::updateConfiguration(const RenderLayer* compositingAncestor)
965{
966 ASSERT(!m_owningLayer.normalFlowListDirty());
967 ASSERT(!m_owningLayer.zOrderListsDirty());
968 ASSERT(!renderer().view().needsLayout());
969
970 bool layerConfigChanged = false;
971 auto& compositor = this->compositor();
972
973 setBackgroundLayerPaintsFixedRootBackground(compositor.needsFixedRootBackgroundLayer(m_owningLayer));
974
975 if (updateBackgroundLayer(m_backgroundLayerPaintsFixedRootBackground || m_requiresBackgroundLayer))
976 layerConfigChanged = true;
977
978 if (updateForegroundLayer(compositor.needsContentsCompositingLayer(m_owningLayer)))
979 layerConfigChanged = true;
980
981 bool needsDescendantsClippingLayer = false;
982 bool usesCompositedScrolling = m_owningLayer.hasCompositedScrollableOverflow();
983
984 if (usesCompositedScrolling) {
985 // If it's scrollable, it has to be a box.
986 FloatRoundedRect contentsClippingRect = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()).roundedBorderBoxRect().pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor());
987 needsDescendantsClippingLayer = contentsClippingRect.isRounded();
988 } else
989 needsDescendantsClippingLayer = RenderLayerCompositor::clipsCompositingDescendants(m_owningLayer);
990
991 if (updateScrollingLayers(usesCompositedScrolling))
992 layerConfigChanged = true;
993
994 if (updateDescendantClippingLayer(needsDescendantsClippingLayer))
995 layerConfigChanged = true;
996
997 ASSERT(compositingAncestor == m_owningLayer.ancestorCompositingLayer());
998 if (updateAncestorClipping(compositor.clippedByAncestor(m_owningLayer, compositingAncestor), compositingAncestor))
999 layerConfigChanged = true;
1000
1001 if (updateOverflowControlsLayers(requiresHorizontalScrollbarLayer(), requiresVerticalScrollbarLayer(), requiresScrollCornerLayer()))
1002 layerConfigChanged = true;
1003
1004 if (layerConfigChanged)
1005 updateInternalHierarchy();
1006
1007 // RenderLayerCompositor::adjustOverflowScrollbarContainerLayers() may have reparented the overflowControlsContainer
1008 // in an earlier update, so always put it back here. We don't yet know if it will get reparented again.
1009 if (m_overflowControlsContainer && m_overflowControlsContainer->parent() != m_graphicsLayer.get()) {
1010 m_graphicsLayer->addChild(*m_overflowControlsContainer);
1011 // Ensure that we fix up the position of m_overflowControlsContainer.
1012 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingGeometryUpdate();
1013 }
1014
1015 // FIXME: Overlow controls need to be above the flattening layer?
1016 if (auto* flatteningLayer = tileCacheFlatteningLayer()) {
1017 if (layerConfigChanged || flatteningLayer->parent() != m_graphicsLayer.get())
1018 m_graphicsLayer->addChild(*flatteningLayer);
1019 }
1020
1021 if (updateMaskingLayer(renderer().hasMask(), renderer().hasClipPath()))
1022 layerConfigChanged = true;
1023
1024 updateChildClippingStrategy(needsDescendantsClippingLayer);
1025
1026 if (m_owningLayer.hasReflection()) {
1027 if (m_owningLayer.reflectionLayer()->backing()) {
1028 auto* reflectionLayer = m_owningLayer.reflectionLayer()->backing()->graphicsLayer();
1029 m_graphicsLayer->setReplicatedByLayer(reflectionLayer);
1030 }
1031 } else
1032 m_graphicsLayer->setReplicatedByLayer(nullptr);
1033
1034 PaintedContentsInfo contentsInfo(*this);
1035
1036 // Requires layout.
1037 if (!m_owningLayer.isRenderViewLayer()) {
1038 bool didUpdateContentsRect = false;
1039 updateDirectlyCompositedBoxDecorations(contentsInfo, didUpdateContentsRect);
1040 } else
1041 updateRootLayerConfiguration();
1042
1043 // Requires layout.
1044 if (contentsInfo.isDirectlyCompositedImage())
1045 updateImageContents(contentsInfo);
1046
1047 if (is<RenderEmbeddedObject>(renderer()) && downcast<RenderEmbeddedObject>(renderer()).allowsAcceleratedCompositing()) {
1048 auto* pluginViewBase = downcast<PluginViewBase>(downcast<RenderWidget>(renderer()).widget());
1049#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1050 if (pluginViewBase && !m_graphicsLayer->contentsLayerForMedia()) {
1051 pluginViewBase->detachPluginLayer();
1052 pluginViewBase->attachPluginLayer();
1053 }
1054#else
1055 if (!pluginViewBase->shouldNotAddLayer())
1056 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsToPlatformLayer(pluginViewBase->platformLayer(), GraphicsLayer::ContentsLayerPurpose::Plugin);
1057#endif
1058 }
1059#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
1060 else if (is<RenderVideo>(renderer()) && downcast<RenderVideo>(renderer()).shouldDisplayVideo()) {
1061 auto* mediaElement = downcast<HTMLMediaElement>(renderer().element());
1062 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsToPlatformLayer(mediaElement->platformLayer(), GraphicsLayer::ContentsLayerPurpose::Media);
1063 updateContentsRects();
1064 }
1065#endif
1066#if ENABLE(WEBGL) || ENABLE(WEBGPU) || ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS)
1067 else if (renderer().isCanvas() && canvasCompositingStrategy(renderer()) == CanvasAsLayerContents) {
1068 const HTMLCanvasElement* canvas = downcast<HTMLCanvasElement>(renderer().element());
1069 if (auto* context = canvas->renderingContext())
1070 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsToPlatformLayer(context->platformLayer(), GraphicsLayer::ContentsLayerPurpose::Canvas);
1071
1072 layerConfigChanged = true;
1073 }
1074#endif
1075#if ENABLE(MODEL_ELEMENT)
1076 else if (is<RenderModel>(renderer())) {
1077 auto element = downcast<HTMLModelElement>(renderer().element());
1078#if HAVE(ARKIT_INLINE_PREVIEW_MAC)
1079 if (auto* platformLayer = element->platformLayer())
1080 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsToPlatformLayer(platformLayer, GraphicsLayer::ContentsLayerPurpose::Model);
1081#else
1082 if (auto model = element->model())
1083 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsToModel(WTFMove(model));
1084#endif
1085
1086 layerConfigChanged = true;
1087 }
1088#endif
1089 if (is<RenderWidget>(renderer()) && compositor.parentFrameContentLayers(downcast<RenderWidget>(renderer()))) {
1090 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingGeometryUpdate();
1091 layerConfigChanged = true;
1092 }
1093
1094 if (RenderLayerCompositor::isCompositedSubframeRenderer(renderer())) {
1095 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsRectClipsDescendants(true);
1096 updateContentsRects();
1097 }
1098
1099 if (layerConfigChanged)
1100 updatePaintingPhases();
1101
1102#if USE(OWNING_LAYER_BEAR_TRAP)
1103 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_owningLayerBearTrap == BEAR_TRAP_VALUE, "RenderLayerBacking::updateConfiguration(): m_owningLayerBearTrap caught the bear (55699292)");
1104 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(&m_owningLayer, "RenderLayerBacking::updateConfiguration(): m_owningLayer is null (55699292)");
1105#endif
1106
1107 return layerConfigChanged;
1108}

1110static bool subpixelOffsetFromRendererChanged(const LayoutSize& oldSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer, const LayoutSize& newSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer, float deviceScaleFactor)
1111{
1112 FloatSize previous = snapSizeToDevicePixel(oldSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer, LayoutPoint(), deviceScaleFactor);
1113 FloatSize current = snapSizeToDevicePixel(newSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer, LayoutPoint(), deviceScaleFactor);
1114 return previous != current;
1115}
1116
1117static FloatSize subpixelForLayerPainting(const LayoutPoint& point, float pixelSnappingFactor)
1118{
1119 LayoutUnit x = point.x();
1120 LayoutUnit y = point.y();
1121 x = x >= 0 ? floorToDevicePixel(x, pixelSnappingFactor) : ceilToDevicePixel(x, pixelSnappingFactor);
1122 y = y >= 0 ? floorToDevicePixel(y, pixelSnappingFactor) : ceilToDevicePixel(y, pixelSnappingFactor);
1123 return point - LayoutPoint(x, y);
1124}
1125
1126struct OffsetFromRenderer {
1127 // 1.2px - > { m_devicePixelOffset = 1px m_subpixelOffset = 0.2px }
1128 LayoutSize m_devicePixelOffset;
1129 LayoutSize m_subpixelOffset;
1130};
1131
1132static OffsetFromRenderer computeOffsetFromRenderer(const LayoutSize& offset, float deviceScaleFactor)
1133{
1134 OffsetFromRenderer offsetFromRenderer;
1135 offsetFromRenderer.m_subpixelOffset = LayoutSize(subpixelForLayerPainting(toLayoutPoint(offset), deviceScaleFactor));
1136 offsetFromRenderer.m_devicePixelOffset = offset - offsetFromRenderer.m_subpixelOffset;
1137 return offsetFromRenderer;
1138}

1140struct SnappedRectInfo {
1141 LayoutRect m_snappedRect;
1142 LayoutSize m_snapDelta;
1143};
1144
1145static SnappedRectInfo snappedGraphicsLayer(const LayoutSize& offset, const LayoutSize& size, float deviceScaleFactor)
1146{
1147 SnappedRectInfo snappedGraphicsLayer;
1148 LayoutRect graphicsLayerRect = LayoutRect(toLayoutPoint(offset), size);
1149 snappedGraphicsLayer.m_snappedRect = LayoutRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(graphicsLayerRect, deviceScaleFactor));
1150 snappedGraphicsLayer.m_snapDelta = snappedGraphicsLayer.m_snappedRect.location() - toLayoutPoint(offset);
1151 return snappedGraphicsLayer;
1152}
1153
1154static LayoutSize computeOffsetFromAncestorGraphicsLayer(const RenderLayer* compositedAncestor, const LayoutPoint& location, float deviceScaleFactor)
1155{
1156 if (!compositedAncestor)
1157 return toLayoutSize(location);
1158
1159 // FIXME: This is a workaround until after webkit.org/b/162634 gets fixed. ancestorSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer
1160 // could be stale when a dynamic composited state change triggers a pre-order updateGeometry() traversal.
1161 LayoutSize ancestorSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer = compositedAncestor->backing()->subpixelOffsetFromRenderer();
1162 LayoutRect ancestorCompositedBounds = compositedAncestor->backing()->compositedBounds();
1163 LayoutSize floored = toLayoutSize(LayoutPoint(floorPointToDevicePixels(ancestorCompositedBounds.location() - ancestorSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer, deviceScaleFactor)));
1164 LayoutSize ancestorRendererOffsetFromAncestorGraphicsLayer = -(floored + ancestorSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer);
1165 return ancestorRendererOffsetFromAncestorGraphicsLayer + toLayoutSize(location);
1166}
1167
1168class ComputedOffsets {
1169public:
1170 ComputedOffsets(const RenderLayer& renderLayer, const RenderLayer* compositingAncestor, const LayoutRect& localRect, const LayoutRect& parentGraphicsLayerRect, const LayoutRect& primaryGraphicsLayerRect)
1171 : m_renderLayer(renderLayer)
1172 , m_compositingAncestor(compositingAncestor)
1173 , m_location(localRect.location())
1174 , m_parentGraphicsLayerOffset(toLayoutSize(parentGraphicsLayerRect.location()))
1175 , m_primaryGraphicsLayerOffset(toLayoutSize(primaryGraphicsLayerRect.location()))
1176 , m_deviceScaleFactor(renderLayer.renderer().document().deviceScaleFactor())
1177 {
1178 }
1179
1180 LayoutSize fromParentGraphicsLayer()
1181 {
1182 if (!m_fromParentGraphicsLayer)
1183 m_fromParentGraphicsLayer = fromAncestorGraphicsLayer() - m_parentGraphicsLayerOffset;
1184 return m_fromParentGraphicsLayer.value();
1185 }
1186
1187 LayoutSize fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer()
1188 {
1189 if (!m_fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer)
1190 m_fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer = fromAncestorGraphicsLayer() - m_parentGraphicsLayerOffset - m_primaryGraphicsLayerOffset;
1191 return m_fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer.value();
1192 }
1193
1194private:
1195 LayoutSize fromAncestorGraphicsLayer()
1196 {
1197 if (!m_fromAncestorGraphicsLayer) {
1198 LayoutPoint localPointInAncestorRenderLayerCoords = m_renderLayer.convertToLayerCoords(m_compositingAncestor, m_location, RenderLayer::AdjustForColumns);
1199 m_fromAncestorGraphicsLayer = computeOffsetFromAncestorGraphicsLayer(m_compositingAncestor, localPointInAncestorRenderLayerCoords, m_deviceScaleFactor);
1200 }
1201 return m_fromAncestorGraphicsLayer.value();
1202 }
1203
1204 std::optional<LayoutSize> m_fromAncestorGraphicsLayer;
1205 std::optional<LayoutSize> m_fromParentGraphicsLayer;
1206 std::optional<LayoutSize> m_fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer;
1207
1208 const RenderLayer& m_renderLayer;
1209 const RenderLayer* m_compositingAncestor;
1210 // Location is relative to the renderer.
1211 const LayoutPoint m_location;
1212 const LayoutSize m_parentGraphicsLayerOffset;
1213 const LayoutSize m_primaryGraphicsLayerOffset;
1214 float m_deviceScaleFactor;
1215};
1216
1217LayoutRect RenderLayerBacking::computePrimaryGraphicsLayerRect(const RenderLayer* compositedAncestor, const LayoutRect& parentGraphicsLayerRect) const
1218{
1219 ComputedOffsets compositedBoundsOffset(m_owningLayer, compositedAncestor, compositedBounds(), parentGraphicsLayerRect, { });
1220 return LayoutRect(encloseRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(toLayoutPoint(compositedBoundsOffset.fromParentGraphicsLayer()), compositedBounds().size()),
1221 deviceScaleFactor()));
1222}
1223
1224// FIXME: See if we need this now that updateGeometry() is always called in post-order traversal.
1225LayoutRect RenderLayerBacking::computeParentGraphicsLayerRect(const RenderLayer* compositedAncestor) const
1226{
1227 if (!compositedAncestor || !compositedAncestor->backing())
1228 return renderer().view().documentRect();
1229
1230 auto* ancestorBacking = compositedAncestor->backing();
1231 LayoutRect parentGraphicsLayerRect;
1232 if (m_owningLayer.isInsideFragmentedFlow()) {
1233 // FIXME: flows/columns need work.
1234 LayoutRect ancestorCompositedBounds = ancestorBacking->compositedBounds();
1235 ancestorCompositedBounds.setLocation(LayoutPoint());
1236 parentGraphicsLayerRect = ancestorCompositedBounds;
1237 }
1238
1239 if (!is<RenderBox>(compositedAncestor->renderer()))
1240 return parentGraphicsLayerRect;
1241
1242 auto& ancestorRenderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(compositedAncestor->renderer());
1243
1244 if (ancestorBacking->hasClippingLayer()) {
1245 // If the compositing ancestor has a layer to clip children, we parent in that, and therefore position relative to it.
1246 LayoutRect clippingBox = clippingLayerBox(ancestorRenderBox);
1247 LayoutSize clippingBoxOffset = computeOffsetFromAncestorGraphicsLayer(compositedAncestor, clippingBox.location(), deviceScaleFactor());
1248 parentGraphicsLayerRect = snappedGraphicsLayer(clippingBoxOffset, clippingBox.size(), deviceScaleFactor()).m_snappedRect;
1249 }
1250
1251 if (compositedAncestor->hasCompositedScrollableOverflow()) {
1252 auto* scrollableArea = compositedAncestor->scrollableArea();
1253 ASSERT(scrollableArea);
1254
1255 LayoutRect ancestorCompositedBounds = ancestorBacking->compositedBounds();
1256 LayoutRect scrollContainerBox = scrollContainerLayerBox(ancestorRenderBox);
1257 ScrollOffset scrollOffset = scrollableArea->scrollOffset();
1258 parentGraphicsLayerRect = LayoutRect((scrollContainerBox.location() - toLayoutSize(ancestorCompositedBounds.location()) - toLayoutSize(scrollOffset)), scrollContainerBox.size());
1259 }
1260
1261 return parentGraphicsLayerRect;
1262}
1263
1264void RenderLayerBacking::updateGeometry(const RenderLayer* compositedAncestor)
1265{
1266 ASSERT(!m_owningLayer.normalFlowListDirty());
1267 ASSERT(!m_owningLayer.zOrderListsDirty());
1268 ASSERT(!m_owningLayer.descendantDependentFlagsAreDirty());
1269 ASSERT(!renderer().view().needsLayout());
1270
1271 const RenderStyle& style = renderer().style();
1272 const auto deviceScaleFactor = this->deviceScaleFactor();
1273
1274 bool isRunningAcceleratedTransformAnimation = false;
1275 if (auto* timeline = renderer().documentTimeline())
1276 isRunningAcceleratedTransformAnimation = timeline->isRunningAcceleratedAnimationOnRenderer(renderer(), CSSPropertyTransform);
1277
1278 updateTransform(style);
1279 updateOpacity(style);
1280 updateFilters(style);
1281#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
1282 updateBackdropFilters(style);
1283#endif
1284#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
1285 updateBlendMode(style);
1286#endif
1287
1288 ASSERT(compositedAncestor == m_owningLayer.ancestorCompositingLayer());
1289 LayoutRect parentGraphicsLayerRect = computeParentGraphicsLayerRect(compositedAncestor);
1290
1291 if (m_ancestorClippingStack)
1292 updateClippingStackLayerGeometry(*m_ancestorClippingStack, compositedAncestor, parentGraphicsLayerRect);
1293
1294 LayoutRect primaryGraphicsLayerRect = computePrimaryGraphicsLayerRect(compositedAncestor, parentGraphicsLayerRect);
1295
1296 ComputedOffsets compositedBoundsOffset(m_owningLayer, compositedAncestor, compositedBounds(), parentGraphicsLayerRect, primaryGraphicsLayerRect);
1297 ComputedOffsets rendererOffset(m_owningLayer, compositedAncestor, { }, parentGraphicsLayerRect, primaryGraphicsLayerRect);
1298
1299 m_compositedBoundsOffsetFromGraphicsLayer = compositedBoundsOffset.fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer();
1300
1301 auto primaryLayerPosition = primaryGraphicsLayerRect.location();
1302
1303 // FIXME: reflections should force transform-style to be flat in the style: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=106959
1304 bool preserves3D = style.transformStyle3D() == TransformStyle3D::Preserve3D && !renderer().hasReflection();
1305 if (m_contentsContainmentLayer) {
1306 m_contentsContainmentLayer->setPreserves3D(preserves3D);
1307 m_contentsContainmentLayer->setPosition(primaryLayerPosition);
1308 primaryLayerPosition = { };
1309 // Use the same size as m_graphicsLayer so transforms behave correctly.
1310 m_contentsContainmentLayer->setSize(primaryGraphicsLayerRect.size());
1311 }
1312
1313 auto computeAnimationExtent = [&] () -> std::optional<FloatRect> {
1314 LayoutRect animatedBounds;
1315 if (isRunningAcceleratedTransformAnimation && m_owningLayer.getOverlapBoundsIncludingChildrenAccountingForTransformAnimations(animatedBounds, RenderLayer::IncludeCompositedDescendants))
1316 return FloatRect(animatedBounds);
1317 return { };
1318 };
1319 m_graphicsLayer->setAnimationExtent(computeAnimationExtent());
1320 m_graphicsLayer->setPreserves3D(preserves3D);
1321 m_graphicsLayer->setBackfaceVisibility(style.backfaceVisibility() == BackfaceVisibility::Visible);
1322
1323 m_graphicsLayer->setPosition(primaryLayerPosition);
1324 m_graphicsLayer->setSize(primaryGraphicsLayerRect.size());
1325
1326#if ENABLE(CSS_TRANSFORM_STYLE_OPTIMIZED_3D)
1327 // FIXME: Take ancestry into account and remove unnecessary structural layers.
1328 m_graphicsLayer->setIsSeparated(style.transformStyle3D() == TransformStyle3D::Optimized3D);
1329#endif
1330
1331 // Compute renderer offset from primary graphics layer. Note that primaryGraphicsLayerRect is in parentGraphicsLayer's coordinate system which is not necessarily
1332 // the same as the ancestor graphics layer.
1333 OffsetFromRenderer primaryGraphicsLayerOffsetFromRenderer;
1334 LayoutSize oldSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer = m_subpixelOffsetFromRenderer;
1335 primaryGraphicsLayerOffsetFromRenderer = computeOffsetFromRenderer(-rendererOffset.fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer(), deviceScaleFactor);
1336 m_subpixelOffsetFromRenderer = primaryGraphicsLayerOffsetFromRenderer.m_subpixelOffset;
1337 m_hasSubpixelRounding = !m_subpixelOffsetFromRenderer.isZero() || compositedBounds().size() != primaryGraphicsLayerRect.size();
1338
1339 if (primaryGraphicsLayerOffsetFromRenderer.m_devicePixelOffset != m_graphicsLayer->offsetFromRenderer())
1340 m_graphicsLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(primaryGraphicsLayerOffsetFromRenderer.m_devicePixelOffset);
1341
1342 // If we have a layer that clips children, position it.
1343 LayoutRect clippingBox;
1344 if (auto* clipLayer = clippingLayer()) {
1345 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer());
1346 // clipLayer is the m_childContainmentLayer.
1347 clippingBox = clippingLayerBox(renderBox);
1348 // Clipping layer is parented in the primary graphics layer.
1349 LayoutSize clipBoxOffsetFromGraphicsLayer = toLayoutSize(clippingBox.location()) + rendererOffset.fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer();
1350 SnappedRectInfo snappedClippingGraphicsLayer = snappedGraphicsLayer(clipBoxOffsetFromGraphicsLayer, clippingBox.size(), deviceScaleFactor);
1351 clipLayer->setPosition(snappedClippingGraphicsLayer.m_snappedRect.location());
1352 clipLayer->setSize(snappedClippingGraphicsLayer.m_snappedRect.size());
1353 clipLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(toLayoutSize(clippingBox.location() - snappedClippingGraphicsLayer.m_snapDelta));
1354
1355 auto computeMasksToBoundsRect = [&] {
1356 if ((renderer().style().clipPath() || renderer().style().hasBorderRadius()) && !m_childClippingMaskLayer) {
1357 FloatRoundedRect contentsClippingRect = renderBox.roundedBorderBoxRect().pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
1358 contentsClippingRect.move(LayoutSize(-clipLayer->offsetFromRenderer()));
1359 return contentsClippingRect;
1360 }
1361
1362 return FloatRoundedRect { FloatRect { { }, snappedClippingGraphicsLayer.m_snappedRect.size() } };
1363 };
1364
1365 clipLayer->setMasksToBoundsRect(computeMasksToBoundsRect());
1366
1367 if (m_childClippingMaskLayer && !m_scrollContainerLayer) {
1368 m_childClippingMaskLayer->setSize(clipLayer->size());
1369 m_childClippingMaskLayer->setPosition({ });
1370 m_childClippingMaskLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(clipLayer->offsetFromRenderer());
1371 }
1372 }
1373
1374 if (m_maskLayer)
1375 updateMaskingLayerGeometry();
1376
1377 updateChildrenTransformAndAnchorPoint(primaryGraphicsLayerRect, rendererOffset.fromParentGraphicsLayer());
1378
1379 if (m_owningLayer.reflectionLayer() && m_owningLayer.reflectionLayer()->isComposited()) {
1380 auto* reflectionBacking = m_owningLayer.reflectionLayer()->backing();
1381 reflectionBacking->updateGeometry(&m_owningLayer);
1382
1383 // The reflection layer has the bounds of m_owningLayer.reflectionLayer(),
1384 // but the reflected layer is the bounds of this layer, so we need to position it appropriately.
1385 FloatRect layerBounds = this->compositedBounds();
1386 FloatRect reflectionLayerBounds = reflectionBacking->compositedBounds();
1387 reflectionBacking->graphicsLayer()->setReplicatedLayerPosition(FloatPoint(layerBounds.location() - reflectionLayerBounds.location()));
1388 }
1389
1390 if (m_scrollContainerLayer) {
1391 ASSERT(m_scrolledContentsLayer);
1392 LayoutRect scrollContainerBox = scrollContainerLayerBox(downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()));
1393 LayoutRect parentLayerBounds = clippingLayer() ? scrollContainerBox : compositedBounds();
1394
1395 // FIXME: need to do some pixel snapping here.
1396 m_scrollContainerLayer->setPosition(FloatPoint(scrollContainerBox.location() - parentLayerBounds.location()));
1397 m_scrollContainerLayer->setSize(roundedIntSize(LayoutSize(scrollContainerBox.width(), scrollContainerBox.height())));
1398
1399 auto* scrollableArea = m_owningLayer.scrollableArea();
1400 ASSERT(scrollableArea);
1401
1402 ScrollOffset scrollOffset = scrollableArea->scrollOffset();
1403 updateScrollOffset(scrollOffset);
1404
1405 FloatSize oldScrollingLayerOffset = m_scrollContainerLayer->offsetFromRenderer();
1406 m_scrollContainerLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(toFloatSize(scrollContainerBox.location()));
1407
1408 if (m_childClippingMaskLayer) {
1409 m_childClippingMaskLayer->setPosition(m_scrollContainerLayer->position());
1410 m_childClippingMaskLayer->setSize(m_scrollContainerLayer->size());
1411 m_childClippingMaskLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(toFloatSize(scrollContainerBox.location()));
1412 }
1413
1414 bool paddingBoxOffsetChanged = oldScrollingLayerOffset != m_scrollContainerLayer->offsetFromRenderer();
1415
1416 IntSize scrollSize;
1417 if (scrollableArea)
1418 scrollSize = IntSize(scrollableArea->scrollWidth(), scrollableArea->scrollHeight());
1419 if (scrollSize != m_scrolledContentsLayer->size() || paddingBoxOffsetChanged)
1420 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setNeedsDisplay();
1421
1422 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setSize(scrollSize);
1423 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setScrollOffset(scrollOffset, GraphicsLayer::DontSetNeedsDisplay);
1424 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(toLayoutSize(scrollContainerBox.location()), GraphicsLayer::DontSetNeedsDisplay);
1425
1426 adjustTiledBackingCoverage();
1427 }
1428
1429 if (m_overflowControlsContainer) {
1430 LayoutRect overflowControlsBox = overflowControlsHostLayerRect(downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()));
1431 LayoutSize boxOffsetFromGraphicsLayer = toLayoutSize(overflowControlsBox.location()) + rendererOffset.fromPrimaryGraphicsLayer();
1432 SnappedRectInfo snappedBoxInfo = snappedGraphicsLayer(boxOffsetFromGraphicsLayer, overflowControlsBox.size(), deviceScaleFactor);
1433
1434 m_overflowControlsContainer->setPosition(snappedBoxInfo.m_snappedRect.location());
1435 m_overflowControlsContainer->setSize(snappedBoxInfo.m_snappedRect.size());
1436 m_overflowControlsContainer->setMasksToBounds(true);
1437 }
1438
1439 if (m_foregroundLayer) {
1440 FloatSize foregroundSize;
1441 FloatSize foregroundOffset;
1442 GraphicsLayer::ShouldSetNeedsDisplay needsDisplayOnOffsetChange = GraphicsLayer::SetNeedsDisplay;
1443 if (m_scrolledContentsLayer) {
1444 foregroundSize = m_scrolledContentsLayer->size();
1445 foregroundOffset = m_scrolledContentsLayer->offsetFromRenderer() - toLayoutSize(m_scrolledContentsLayer->scrollOffset());
1446 needsDisplayOnOffsetChange = GraphicsLayer::DontSetNeedsDisplay;
1447 } else if (hasClippingLayer()) {
1448 // If we have a clipping layer (which clips descendants), then the foreground layer is a child of it,
1449 // so that it gets correctly sorted with children. In that case, position relative to the clipping layer.
1450 foregroundSize = FloatSize(clippingBox.size());
1451 foregroundOffset = toFloatSize(clippingBox.location());
1452 } else {
1453 foregroundSize = primaryGraphicsLayerRect.size();
1454 foregroundOffset = m_graphicsLayer->offsetFromRenderer();
1455 }
1456
1457 m_foregroundLayer->setPosition({ });
1458 m_foregroundLayer->setSize(foregroundSize);
1459 m_foregroundLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(foregroundOffset, needsDisplayOnOffsetChange);
1460 }
1461
1462 if (m_backgroundLayer) {
1463 FloatPoint backgroundPosition;
1464 FloatSize backgroundSize = primaryGraphicsLayerRect.size();
1465 if (backgroundLayerPaintsFixedRootBackground()) {
1466 const FrameView& frameView = renderer().view().frameView();
1467 backgroundPosition = frameView.scrollPositionForFixedPosition();
1468 backgroundSize = frameView.layoutSize();
1469 } else {
1470 auto boundingBox = renderer().objectBoundingBox();
1471 backgroundPosition = boundingBox.location();
1472 backgroundSize = boundingBox.size();
1473 }
1474 m_backgroundLayer->setPosition(backgroundPosition);
1475 m_backgroundLayer->setSize(backgroundSize);
1476 m_backgroundLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(m_graphicsLayer->offsetFromRenderer());
1477 }
1478
1479 // If this layer was created just for clipping or to apply perspective, it doesn't need its own backing store.
1480 LayoutRect ancestorCompositedBounds = compositedAncestor ? compositedAncestor->backing()->compositedBounds() : LayoutRect();
1481 setRequiresOwnBackingStore(compositor().requiresOwnBackingStore(m_owningLayer, compositedAncestor,
1482 LayoutRect(toLayoutPoint(compositedBoundsOffset.fromParentGraphicsLayer()), compositedBounds().size()), ancestorCompositedBounds));
1483#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
1484 updateBackdropFiltersGeometry();
1485#endif
1486 updateAfterWidgetResize();
1487
1488 positionOverflowControlsLayers();
1489
1490 if (subpixelOffsetFromRendererChanged(oldSubpixelOffsetFromRenderer, m_subpixelOffsetFromRenderer, deviceScaleFactor) && canIssueSetNeedsDisplay())
1491 setContentsNeedDisplay();
1492}

1494void RenderLayerBacking::adjustOverflowControlsPositionRelativeToAncestor(const RenderLayer& ancestorLayer)
1495{
1496 ASSERT(m_overflowControlsContainer);
1497 ASSERT(ancestorLayer.isComposited());
1498 auto ancestorBacking = ancestorLayer.backing();
1499 if (!ancestorBacking)
1500 return;
1501
1502 LayoutRect parentGraphicsLayerRect = computeParentGraphicsLayerRect(&ancestorLayer);
1503 LayoutRect primaryGraphicsLayerRect = computePrimaryGraphicsLayerRect(&ancestorLayer, parentGraphicsLayerRect);
1504
1505 auto overflowControlsRect = overflowControlsHostLayerRect(downcast<RenderBox>(renderer()));
1506
1507 if (overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack())
1508 updateClippingStackLayerGeometry(*m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack, &ancestorLayer, parentGraphicsLayerRect);
1509
1510 ComputedOffsets rendererOffset(m_owningLayer, &ancestorLayer, { }, parentGraphicsLayerRect, primaryGraphicsLayerRect);
1511
1512 LayoutSize boxOffsetFromGraphicsLayer = toLayoutSize(overflowControlsRect.location()) + rendererOffset.fromParentGraphicsLayer();
1513 SnappedRectInfo snappedBoxInfo = snappedGraphicsLayer(boxOffsetFromGraphicsLayer, overflowControlsRect.size(), deviceScaleFactor());
1514
1515 m_overflowControlsContainer->setPosition(snappedBoxInfo.m_snappedRect.location());
1516 m_overflowControlsContainer->setSize(snappedBoxInfo.m_snappedRect.size());
1517}

1519void RenderLayerBacking::setLocationOfScrolledContents(ScrollOffset scrollOffset, ScrollingLayerPositionAction setOrSync)
1520{
1521 if (setOrSync == ScrollingLayerPositionAction::Sync)
1522 m_scrollContainerLayer->syncBoundsOrigin(scrollOffset);
1523 else
1524 m_scrollContainerLayer->setBoundsOrigin(scrollOffset);
1525}

1527void RenderLayerBacking::updateScrollOffset(ScrollOffset scrollOffset)
1528{
1529 auto* scrollableArea = m_owningLayer.scrollableArea();
1530 ASSERT(scrollableArea);
1531
1532 if (scrollableArea->currentScrollType() == ScrollType::User) {
1533 // If scrolling is happening externally, we don't want to touch the layer bounds origin here because that will cause jitter.
1534 setLocationOfScrolledContents(scrollOffset, ScrollingLayerPositionAction::Sync);
1535 scrollableArea->setRequiresScrollPositionReconciliation(true);
1536 } else {
1537 // Note that we implement the contents offset via the bounds origin on this layer, rather than a position on the sublayer.
1538 setLocationOfScrolledContents(scrollOffset, ScrollingLayerPositionAction::Set);
1539 scrollableArea->setRequiresScrollPositionReconciliation(false);
1540 }
1541
1542 ASSERT(m_scrolledContentsLayer->position().isZero());
1543}

1545void RenderLayerBacking::updateAfterDescendants()
1546{
1547 // FIXME: this potentially duplicates work we did in updateConfiguration().
1548 PaintedContentsInfo contentsInfo(*this);
1549 contentsInfo.setWantsSubpixelAntialiasedTextState(GraphicsLayer::supportsSubpixelAntialiasedLayerText() && FontCascade::isSubpixelAntialiasingAvailable());
1550
1551 if (!m_owningLayer.isRenderViewLayer()) {
1552 bool didUpdateContentsRect = false;
1553 updateDirectlyCompositedBoxDecorations(contentsInfo, didUpdateContentsRect);
1554 if (!didUpdateContentsRect && m_graphicsLayer->usesContentsLayer())
1555 resetContentsRect();
1556 }
1557
1558 updateDrawsContent(contentsInfo);
1559
1560 if (!m_isMainFrameRenderViewLayer && !m_isFrameLayerWithTiledBacking && !m_requiresBackgroundLayer) {
1561 // For non-root layers, background is always painted by the primary graphics layer.
1562 ASSERT(!m_backgroundLayer);
1563 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsOpaque(!m_hasSubpixelRounding && m_owningLayer.backgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(compositedBounds()));
1564 }
1565
1566 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsVisible(m_owningLayer.hasVisibleContent() || hasVisibleNonCompositedDescendants());
1567 if (m_scrollContainerLayer) {
1568 m_scrollContainerLayer->setContentsVisible(renderer().style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible);
1569
1570 bool userInteractive = renderer().style().pointerEvents() != PointerEvents::None;
1571 m_scrollContainerLayer->setUserInteractionEnabled(userInteractive);
1572 if (m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar)
1573 m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar->setUserInteractionEnabled(userInteractive);
1574 if (m_layerForVerticalScrollbar)
1575 m_layerForVerticalScrollbar->setUserInteractionEnabled(userInteractive);
1576 if (m_layerForScrollCorner)
1577 m_layerForScrollCorner->setUserInteractionEnabled(userInteractive);
1578 }
1579
1580#if USE(OWNING_LAYER_BEAR_TRAP)
1581 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_owningLayerBearTrap == BEAR_TRAP_VALUE, "RenderLayerBacking::updateAfterDescendants(): m_owningLayerBearTrap caught the bear (55699292)");
1582 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(&m_owningLayer, "RenderLayerBacking::updateAfterDescendants(): m_owningLayer is null (55699292)");
1583#endif
1584}

1586// FIXME: Avoid repaints when clip path changes.
1587void RenderLayerBacking::updateMaskingLayerGeometry()
1588{
1589 m_maskLayer->setSize(m_graphicsLayer->size());
1590 m_maskLayer->setPosition(FloatPoint());
1591 m_maskLayer->setOffsetFromRenderer(m_graphicsLayer->offsetFromRenderer());
1592
1593 if (!m_maskLayer->drawsContent()) {
1594 if (renderer().hasClipPath()) {
1595 ASSERT(renderer().style().clipPath()->type() != ClipPathOperation::Reference);
1596
1597 WindRule windRule;
1598 // FIXME: Use correct reference box for inlines: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=129047
1599 LayoutRect boundingBox = m_owningLayer.boundingBox(&m_owningLayer);
1600 LayoutRect referenceBoxForClippedInline = LayoutRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(boundingBox, deviceScaleFactor()));
1601 LayoutSize offset = LayoutSize(snapSizeToDevicePixel(-m_subpixelOffsetFromRenderer, LayoutPoint(), deviceScaleFactor()));
1602 Path clipPath = m_owningLayer.computeClipPath(offset, referenceBoxForClippedInline, windRule);
1603
1604 FloatSize pathOffset = m_maskLayer->offsetFromRenderer();
1605 if (!pathOffset.isZero())
1606 clipPath.translate(-pathOffset);
1607
1608 m_maskLayer->setShapeLayerPath(clipPath);
1609 m_maskLayer->setShapeLayerWindRule(windRule);
1610 }
1611 }
1612}

1614void RenderLayerBacking::updateDirectlyCompositedBoxDecorations(PaintedContentsInfo& contentsInfo, bool& didUpdateContentsRect)
1615{
1616 if (!m_owningLayer.hasVisibleContent())
1617 return;
1618
1619 // The order of operations here matters, since the last valid type of contents needs
1620 // to also update the contentsRect.
1621 updateDirectlyCompositedBackgroundColor(contentsInfo, didUpdateContentsRect);
1622 updateDirectlyCompositedBackgroundImage(contentsInfo, didUpdateContentsRect);
1623}
1624
1625void RenderLayerBacking::updateInternalHierarchy()
1626{
1627 // m_foregroundLayer has to be inserted in the correct order with child layers,
1628 // so it's not inserted here.
1629 GraphicsLayer* lastClippingLayer = nullptr;
1630 if (m_ancestorClippingStack) {
1631 connectClippingStackLayers(*m_ancestorClippingStack);
1632 lastClippingLayer = m_ancestorClippingStack->lastClippingLayer();
1633 }
1634
1635 if (m_contentsContainmentLayer) {
1636 m_contentsContainmentLayer->removeAllChildren();
1637 if (lastClippingLayer)
1638 lastClippingLayer->addChild(*m_contentsContainmentLayer);
1639 }
1640
1641 if (m_backgroundLayer)
1642 m_contentsContainmentLayer->addChild(*m_backgroundLayer);
1643
1644 if (m_contentsContainmentLayer)
1645 m_contentsContainmentLayer->addChild(*m_graphicsLayer);
1646 else if (lastClippingLayer)
1647 lastClippingLayer->addChild(*m_graphicsLayer);
1648
1649 if (m_childContainmentLayer)
1650 m_graphicsLayer->addChild(*m_childContainmentLayer);
1651
1652 if (m_scrollContainerLayer) {
1653 auto* superlayer = m_childContainmentLayer ? m_childContainmentLayer.get() : m_graphicsLayer.get();
1654 superlayer->addChild(*m_scrollContainerLayer);
1655 }
1656
1657 // The clip for child layers does not include space for overflow controls, so they exist as
1658 // siblings of the clipping layer if we have one. Normal children of this layer are set as
1659 // children of the clipping layer.
1660 if (m_overflowControlsContainer) {
1661 if (m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar)
1662 m_overflowControlsContainer->addChild(*m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar);
1663
1664 if (m_layerForVerticalScrollbar)
1665 m_overflowControlsContainer->addChild(*m_layerForVerticalScrollbar);
1666
1667 if (m_layerForScrollCorner)
1668 m_overflowControlsContainer->addChild(*m_layerForScrollCorner);
1669
1670 // m_overflowControlsContainer may get reparented later.
1671 m_graphicsLayer->addChild(*m_overflowControlsContainer);
1672 }
1673}

1677 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(contentsBox(), deviceScaleFactor()));
1678
1679 if (is<RenderReplaced>(renderer())) {
1680 FloatRoundedRect contentsClippingRect = downcast<RenderReplaced>(renderer()).roundedContentBoxRect().pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor());
1681 contentsClippingRect.move(contentOffsetInCompositingLayer());
1682 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsClippingRect(contentsClippingRect);
1683 }
1684}

1688 updateContentsRects();
1689 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsTileSize(IntSize());
1690 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsTilePhase(IntSize());
1691}

1695 PaintedContentsInfo contentsInfo(*this);
1696 contentsInfo.setWantsSubpixelAntialiasedTextState(GraphicsLayer::supportsSubpixelAntialiasedLayerText());
1697
1698 updateDrawsContent(contentsInfo);
1699}
1700
1701void RenderLayerBacking::updateDrawsContent(PaintedContentsInfo& contentsInfo)
1702{
1703 if (m_scrollContainerLayer) {
1704 // We don't have to consider overflow controls, because we know that the scrollbars are drawn elsewhere.
1705 // m_graphicsLayer only needs backing store if the non-scrolling parts (background, outlines, borders, shadows etc) need to paint.
1706 // m_scrollContainerLayer never has backing store.
1707 // m_scrolledContentsLayer only needs backing store if the scrolled contents need to paint.
1708 bool hasNonScrollingPaintedContent = m_owningLayer.hasVisibleContent() && m_owningLayer.hasVisibleBoxDecorationsOrBackground();
1709 m_graphicsLayer->setDrawsContent(hasNonScrollingPaintedContent);
1710
1711 bool hasScrollingPaintedContent = hasBackingSharingLayers() || (m_owningLayer.hasVisibleContent() && (renderer().hasBackground() || contentsInfo.paintsContent()));
1712 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setDrawsContent(hasScrollingPaintedContent);
1713 return;
1714 }
1715
1716 bool hasPaintedContent = containsPaintedContent(contentsInfo);
1717
1718 m_paintsSubpixelAntialiasedText = renderer().settings().subpixelAntialiasedLayerTextEnabled() && contentsInfo.paintsSubpixelAntialiasedText();
1719
1720 // FIXME: we could refine this to only allocate backing for one of these layers if possible.
1721 m_graphicsLayer->setDrawsContent(hasPaintedContent);
1722 if (m_foregroundLayer) {
1723 m_foregroundLayer->setDrawsContent(hasPaintedContent);
1724 m_foregroundLayer->setSupportsSubpixelAntialiasedText(m_paintsSubpixelAntialiasedText);
1725 // The text content is painted into the foreground layer.
1726 // FIXME: this ignores SVG background images which may contain text.
1727 m_graphicsLayer->setSupportsSubpixelAntialiasedText(false);
1728 } else
1729 m_graphicsLayer->setSupportsSubpixelAntialiasedText(m_paintsSubpixelAntialiasedText);
1730
1731 if (m_backgroundLayer)
1732 m_backgroundLayer->setDrawsContent(m_backgroundLayerPaintsFixedRootBackground ? hasPaintedContent : contentsInfo.paintsBoxDecorations());
1733}
1734
1735#if ENABLE(ASYNC_SCROLLING)
1736bool RenderLayerBacking::maintainsEventRegion() const
1737{
1738 if (!m_owningLayer.page().scrollingCoordinator())
1739 return false;
1740
1741 if (paintsIntoCompositedAncestor())
1742 return false;
1743
1744 if (renderer().view().needsEventRegionUpdateForNonCompositedFrame())
1745 return true;
1746
1747#if ENABLE(TOUCH_ACTION_REGIONS)
1748 if (renderer().document().mayHaveElementsWithNonAutoTouchAction())
1749 return true;
1750#endif
1751#if ENABLE(EDITABLE_REGION)
1752 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << "RenderLayerBacking: " << this << " maintainsEventRegion - mayHaveEditableElements: " << renderer().document().mayHaveEditableElements() << " shouldBuildEditableRegion: " << renderer().page().shouldBuildEditableRegion());
1753 if (renderer().document().mayHaveEditableElements() && renderer().page().shouldBuildEditableRegion())
1754 return true;
1755#endif
1756#if ENABLE(WHEEL_EVENT_REGIONS)
1757 if (renderer().document().hasWheelEventHandlers())
1758 return true;
1759#endif
1760 if (m_owningLayer.isRenderViewLayer())
1761 return false;
1762
1763 auto& settings = renderer().settings();
1764 if (!settings.asyncFrameScrollingEnabled() && !settings.asyncOverflowScrollingEnabled())
1765 return false;
1766
1767 if (!m_owningLayer.page().scrollingCoordinator()->hasSubscrollers())
1768 return false;
1769
1770 return true;
1771}
1772
1773void RenderLayerBacking::updateEventRegion()
1774{
1775 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventRegions, stream << m_owningLayer << " " << this << " updateEventRegion (needs update: " << needsEventRegionUpdate() << ", maintainsEventRegion: " << maintainsEventRegion() << ")");
1776
1777 if (!maintainsEventRegion())
1778 return;
1779
1780 if (!needsEventRegionUpdate())
1781 return;
1782
1783 TraceScope scope(ComputeEventRegionsStart, ComputeEventRegionsEnd);
1784
1785 auto visibleToHitTesting = renderer().visibleToHitTesting();
1786
1787 auto setEventRegionToLayerBounds = [&](GraphicsLayer* graphicsLayer) {
1788 if (!graphicsLayer)
1789 return;
1790
1791 EventRegion eventRegion;
1792 auto eventRegionContext = eventRegion.makeContext();
1793 if (visibleToHitTesting)
1794 eventRegionContext.unite(enclosingIntRect(FloatRect({ }, graphicsLayer->size())), renderer().style());
1795
1796 graphicsLayer->setEventRegion(WTFMove(eventRegion));
1797 };
1798
1799 auto updateEventRegionForLayer = [&](GraphicsLayer& graphicsLayer) {
1800 NullGraphicsContext nullContext(NullGraphicsContext::PaintInvalidationReasons::None);
1801 EventRegion eventRegion;
1802#if ENABLE(EDITABLE_REGION)
1803 if (renderer().page().shouldBuildEditableRegion())
1804 eventRegion.ensureEditableRegion();
1805#endif
1806 auto eventRegionContext = eventRegion.makeContext();
1807 auto layerOffset = graphicsLayer.scrollOffset() - roundedIntSize(graphicsLayer.offsetFromRenderer());
1808
1809 if (visibleToHitTesting) {
1810 if (&graphicsLayer == m_scrolledContentsLayer) {
1811 // Initialize scrolled contents layer with layer-sized event region as it can all used for scrolling.
1812 // This avoids generating unnecessarily complex event regions. We still need to to do the paint to capture touch-action regions.
1813 eventRegionContext.unite(enclosingIntRect(FloatRect(-layerOffset, graphicsLayer.size())), renderer().style());
1814 }
1815 }
1816
1817 if (m_owningLayer.isRenderViewLayer() && (&graphicsLayer == m_graphicsLayer || &graphicsLayer == m_foregroundLayer)) {
1818 // Event handlers on the root cover the entire layer.
1819 eventRegionContext.unite(enclosingIntRect(FloatRect(-layerOffset, graphicsLayer.size())), renderer().style());
1820 }
1821
1822 auto dirtyRect = enclosingIntRect(FloatRect(FloatPoint(graphicsLayer.offsetFromRenderer()), graphicsLayer.size()));
1823 paintIntoLayer(&graphicsLayer, nullContext, dirtyRect, { }, &eventRegionContext);
1824
1825 eventRegion.translate(toIntSize(layerOffset));
1826
1827 graphicsLayer.setEventRegion(WTFMove(eventRegion));
1828 };
1829
1830 updateEventRegionForLayer(*m_graphicsLayer);
1831
1832 setEventRegionToLayerBounds(m_scrollContainerLayer.get());
1833 setEventRegionToLayerBounds(m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar.get());
1834 setEventRegionToLayerBounds(m_layerForVerticalScrollbar.get());
1835 setEventRegionToLayerBounds(m_layerForScrollCorner.get());
1836
1837 if (m_scrolledContentsLayer)
1838 updateEventRegionForLayer(*m_scrolledContentsLayer);
1839
1840 if (m_foregroundLayer)
1841 updateEventRegionForLayer(*m_foregroundLayer);
1842
1843 renderer().view().setNeedsEventRegionUpdateForNonCompositedFrame(false);
1844
1845 setNeedsEventRegionUpdate(false);
1846}
1847#endif

1849bool RenderLayerBacking::updateAncestorClippingStack(Vector<CompositedClipData>&& clippingData)
1850{
1851 if (!m_ancestorClippingStack && clippingData.isEmpty())
1852 return false;
1853
1854 auto* scrollingCoordinator = m_owningLayer.page().scrollingCoordinator();
1855
1856 if (m_ancestorClippingStack && clippingData.isEmpty()) {
1857 m_ancestorClippingStack->clear(scrollingCoordinator);
1858 m_ancestorClippingStack = nullptr;
1859
1860 if (m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack) {
1861 m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack->clear(scrollingCoordinator);
1862 m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack = nullptr;
1863 }
1864 return true;
1865 }
1866
1867 if (!m_ancestorClippingStack) {
1868 m_ancestorClippingStack = makeUnique<LayerAncestorClippingStack>(WTFMove(clippingData));
1869 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "layer " << &m_owningLayer << " ancestorClippingStack " << *m_ancestorClippingStack);
1870 return true;
1871 }
1872
1873 if (m_ancestorClippingStack->equalToClipData(clippingData)) {
1874 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "layer " << &m_owningLayer << " ancestorClippingStack " << *m_ancestorClippingStack);
1875 return false;
1876 }
1877
1878 m_ancestorClippingStack->updateWithClipData(scrollingCoordinator, WTFMove(clippingData));
1879 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "layer " << &m_owningLayer << " ancestorClippingStack " << *m_ancestorClippingStack);
1880 if (m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack)
1881 m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack->updateWithClipData(scrollingCoordinator, WTFMove(clippingData));
1882 return true;
1883}

1885void RenderLayerBacking::ensureOverflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack(const RenderLayer* compositedAncestor)
1886{
1887 auto* scrollingCoordinator = m_owningLayer.page().scrollingCoordinator();
1888 auto clippingData = m_ancestorClippingStack->compositedClipData();
1889
1890 if (m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack)
1891 m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack->updateWithClipData(scrollingCoordinator, WTFMove(clippingData));
1892 else
1893 m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack = makeUnique<LayerAncestorClippingStack>(WTFMove(clippingData));
1894
1895 ensureClippingStackLayers(*m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack);
1896
1897 LayoutRect parentGraphicsLayerRect = computeParentGraphicsLayerRect(compositedAncestor);
1898 updateClippingStackLayerGeometry(*m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack, compositedAncestor, parentGraphicsLayerRect);
1899
1900 connectClippingStackLayers(*m_overflowControlsHostLayerAncestorClippingStack);
1901}

1908 entry.clippingLayer->setMasksToBounds(true);

1910 }
1911 }

1920void RenderLayerBacking::connectClippingStackLayers(LayerAncestorClippingStack& clippingStack)
1921{
1922 auto& clippingEntryStack = clippingStack.stack();
1923 for (unsigned i = 0; i < clippingEntryStack.size() - 1; ++i) {
1924 auto& entry = clippingEntryStack.at(i);
1925 Vector<Ref<GraphicsLayer>> children;
1926 children.append(*clippingEntryStack.at(i + 1).clippingLayer);
1927 entry.clippingLayer->setChildren(WTFMove(children));
1928 }
1929
1930 clippingEntryStack.last().clippingLayer->removeAllChildren();
1931}

1933void RenderLayerBacking::updateClippingStackLayerGeometry(LayerAncestorClippingStack& clippingStack, const RenderLayer* compositedAncestor, LayoutRect& parentGraphicsLayerRect)
1934{
1935 // All clipRects in the stack are computed relative to m_owningLayer, so convert them back to compositedAncestor.
1936 auto offsetFromCompositedAncestor = toLayoutSize(m_owningLayer.convertToLayerCoords(compositedAncestor, { }, RenderLayer::AdjustForColumns));
1937 LayoutRect lastClipLayerRect = parentGraphicsLayerRect;
1938
1939 auto deviceScaleFactor = this->deviceScaleFactor();
1940 for (auto& entry : clippingStack.stack()) {
1941 auto clipRect = entry.clipData.clipRect;
1942 LayoutSize clippingOffset = computeOffsetFromAncestorGraphicsLayer(compositedAncestor, clipRect.location() + offsetFromCompositedAncestor, deviceScaleFactor);
1943 LayoutRect snappedClippingLayerRect = snappedGraphicsLayer(clippingOffset, clipRect.size(), deviceScaleFactor).m_snappedRect;
1944
1945 entry.clippingLayer->setPosition(toLayoutPoint(snappedClippingLayerRect.location() - lastClipLayerRect.location()));
1946 lastClipLayerRect = snappedClippingLayerRect;
1947
1948 entry.clippingLayer->setSize(snappedClippingLayerRect.size());
1949
1950 if (entry.clipData.isOverflowScroll) {
1951 ScrollOffset scrollOffset;
1952 if (auto* scrollableArea = entry.clipData.clippingLayer ? entry.clipData.clippingLayer->scrollableArea() : nullptr)
1953 scrollOffset = scrollableArea->scrollOffset();
1954
1955 entry.clippingLayer->setBoundsOrigin(scrollOffset);
1956 lastClipLayerRect.moveBy(-scrollOffset);
1957 } else
1958 entry.clippingLayer->setBoundsOrigin({ });
1959 }
1960
1961 parentGraphicsLayerRect = lastClipLayerRect;
1962}

2085bool RenderLayerBacking::updateOverflowControlsLayers(bool needsHorizontalScrollbarLayer, bool needsVerticalScrollbarLayer, bool needsScrollCornerLayer)
2086{
2087 auto createOrDestroyLayer = [&](RefPtr<GraphicsLayer>& layer, bool needLayer, bool drawsContent, const char* layerName) {
2088 if (needLayer == !!layer)
2089 return false;
2090
2091 if (needLayer) {
2092 layer = createGraphicsLayer(layerName);
2093 if (drawsContent)
2094 layer->setAllowsBackingStoreDetaching(false);
2095 else {
2096 layer->setPaintingPhase({ });
2097 layer->setDrawsContent(false);
2098 }
2099 } else {
2100 willDestroyLayer(layer.get());
2101 GraphicsLayer::unparentAndClear(layer);
2102 }
2103 return true;
2104 };
2105
2106 bool layersChanged = createOrDestroyLayer(m_overflowControlsContainer, needsHorizontalScrollbarLayer || needsVerticalScrollbarLayer || needsScrollCornerLayer, false, "overflow controls container");
2107
2108 bool horizontalScrollbarLayerChanged = createOrDestroyLayer(m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar, needsHorizontalScrollbarLayer, true, "horizontal scrollbar");
2109 layersChanged |= horizontalScrollbarLayerChanged;
2110
2111 bool verticalScrollbarLayerChanged = createOrDestroyLayer(m_layerForVerticalScrollbar, needsVerticalScrollbarLayer, true, "vertical scrollbar");
2112 layersChanged |= verticalScrollbarLayerChanged;
2113
2114 layersChanged |= createOrDestroyLayer(m_layerForScrollCorner, needsScrollCornerLayer, true, "scroll corner");
2115
2116 if (auto* scrollingCoordinator = m_owningLayer.page().scrollingCoordinator()) {
2117 if (auto* scrollableArea = m_owningLayer.scrollableArea()) {
2118 if (horizontalScrollbarLayerChanged)
2119 scrollingCoordinator->scrollableAreaScrollbarLayerDidChange(*scrollableArea, HorizontalScrollbar);
2120 if (verticalScrollbarLayerChanged)
2121 scrollingCoordinator->scrollableAreaScrollbarLayerDidChange(*scrollableArea, VerticalScrollbar);
2122 }
2123 }
2124
2125 return layersChanged;
2126}

2129{

2226// Masking layer is used for masks or clip-path.
2227bool RenderLayerBacking::updateMaskingLayer(bool hasMask, bool hasClipPath)
2228{
2229 bool layerChanged = false;
2230 if (hasMask || hasClipPath) {
2231 OptionSet<GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase> maskPhases;
2232 if (hasMask)
2233 maskPhases = GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Mask;
2234
2235 if (hasClipPath) {
2236 // If we have a mask, we need to paint the combined clip-path and mask into the mask layer.
2237 if (hasMask || renderer().style().clipPath()->type() == ClipPathOperation::Reference || !GraphicsLayer::supportsLayerType(GraphicsLayer::Type::Shape))
2238 maskPhases.add(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::ClipPath);
2239 }
2240
2241 bool paintsContent = !maskPhases.isEmpty();
2242 GraphicsLayer::Type requiredLayerType = paintsContent ? GraphicsLayer::Type::Normal : GraphicsLayer::Type::Shape;
2243 if (m_maskLayer && m_maskLayer->type() != requiredLayerType) {
2244 m_graphicsLayer->setMaskLayer(nullptr);
2245 willDestroyLayer(m_maskLayer.get());
2246 GraphicsLayer::clear(m_maskLayer);
2247 }
2248
2249 if (!m_maskLayer) {
2250 m_maskLayer = createGraphicsLayer("mask", requiredLayerType);
2251 m_maskLayer->setDrawsContent(paintsContent);
2252 m_maskLayer->setPaintingPhase(maskPhases);
2253 layerChanged = true;
2254 m_graphicsLayer->setMaskLayer(m_maskLayer.copyRef());
2255 // We need a geometry update to size the new mask layer.
2256 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingGeometryUpdate();
2257 }
2258 } else if (m_maskLayer) {
2259 m_graphicsLayer->setMaskLayer(nullptr);
2260 willDestroyLayer(m_maskLayer.get());
2261 GraphicsLayer::clear(m_maskLayer);
2262 layerChanged = true;
2263 }
