2321void RenderLayerBacking::detachFromScrollingCoordinator(OptionSet<ScrollCoordinationRole> roles)
2322{
2323 if (!m_scrollingNodeID && !m_ancestorClippingStack && !m_frameHostingNodeID && !m_viewportConstrainedNodeID && !m_positioningNodeID)
2324 return;
2325
2326 auto* scrollingCoordinator = m_owningLayer.page().scrollingCoordinator();
2327 if (!scrollingCoordinator)
2328 return;
2329
2330 if (roles.contains(ScrollCoordinationRole::Scrolling) && m_scrollingNodeID) {
2331 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "Detaching Scrolling node " << m_scrollingNodeID);
2332 scrollingCoordinator->unparentChildrenAndDestroyNode(m_scrollingNodeID);
2333 m_scrollingNodeID = 0;
2334
2335#if ENABLE(SCROLLING_THREAD)
2336 if (m_scrollContainerLayer)
2337 m_scrollContainerLayer->setScrollingNodeID(0);
2338 if (m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar)
2339 m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar->setScrollingNodeID(0);
2340 if (m_layerForVerticalScrollbar)
2341 m_layerForVerticalScrollbar->setScrollingNodeID(0);
2342 if (m_layerForScrollCorner)
2343 m_layerForScrollCorner->setScrollingNodeID(0);
2344#endif
2345 }
2346
2347 if (roles.contains(ScrollCoordinationRole::ScrollingProxy) && m_ancestorClippingStack) {
2348 m_ancestorClippingStack->detachFromScrollingCoordinator(*scrollingCoordinator);
2349 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "Detaching nodes in ancestor clipping stack");
2350 }
2351
2352 if (roles.contains(ScrollCoordinationRole::FrameHosting) && m_frameHostingNodeID) {
2353 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "Detaching FrameHosting node " << m_frameHostingNodeID);
2354 scrollingCoordinator->unparentChildrenAndDestroyNode(m_frameHostingNodeID);
2355 m_frameHostingNodeID = 0;
2356 }
2357
2358 if (roles.contains(ScrollCoordinationRole::ViewportConstrained) && m_viewportConstrainedNodeID) {
2359 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "Detaching ViewportConstrained node " << m_viewportConstrainedNodeID);
2360 scrollingCoordinator->unparentChildrenAndDestroyNode(m_viewportConstrainedNodeID);
2361 m_viewportConstrainedNodeID = 0;
2362 }
2363
2364 if (roles.contains(ScrollCoordinationRole::Positioning) && m_positioningNodeID) {
2365 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Compositing, stream << "Detaching Positioned node " << m_positioningNodeID);
2366 scrollingCoordinator->unparentChildrenAndDestroyNode(m_positioningNodeID);
2367 m_positioningNodeID = 0;
2368#if ENABLE(SCROLLING_THREAD)
2369 m_graphicsLayer->setScrollingNodeID(0);
2370#endif
2371 }
2372}
2373
2374void RenderLayerBacking::setScrollingNodeIDForRole(ScrollingNodeID nodeID, ScrollCoordinationRole role)
2375{
2376 switch (role) {
2377 case ScrollCoordinationRole::Scrolling:
2378 m_scrollingNodeID = nodeID;
2379#if ENABLE(SCROLLING_THREAD)
2380 if (m_scrollContainerLayer)
2381 m_scrollContainerLayer->setScrollingNodeID(m_scrollingNodeID);
2382
2383 if (m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar)
2384 m_layerForHorizontalScrollbar->setScrollingNodeID(m_scrollingNodeID);
2385 if (m_layerForVerticalScrollbar)
2386 m_layerForVerticalScrollbar->setScrollingNodeID(m_scrollingNodeID);
2387 if (m_layerForScrollCorner)
2388 m_layerForScrollCorner->setScrollingNodeID(m_scrollingNodeID);
2389#endif
2390 break;
2391 case ScrollCoordinationRole::ScrollingProxy:
2392 // These nodeIDs are stored in m_ancestorClippingStack.
2393 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2394 break;
2395 case ScrollCoordinationRole::FrameHosting:
2396 m_frameHostingNodeID = nodeID;
2397 break;
2398 case ScrollCoordinationRole::ViewportConstrained:
2399 m_viewportConstrainedNodeID = nodeID;
2400 break;
2401 case ScrollCoordinationRole::Positioning:
2402 m_positioningNodeID = nodeID;
2403#if ENABLE(SCROLLING_THREAD)
2404 m_graphicsLayer->setScrollingNodeID(m_positioningNodeID);
2405#endif
2406 break;
2407 }
2408}

2410ScrollingNodeID RenderLayerBacking::scrollingNodeIDForChildren() const
2411{
2412 if (m_frameHostingNodeID)
2413 return m_frameHostingNodeID;
2414
2415 if (m_scrollingNodeID)
2416 return m_scrollingNodeID;
2417
2418 if (m_viewportConstrainedNodeID)
2419 return m_viewportConstrainedNodeID;
2420
2421 if (m_ancestorClippingStack) {
2422 if (auto lastOverflowScrollProxyNode = m_ancestorClippingStack->lastOverflowScrollProxyNodeID())
2423 return lastOverflowScrollProxyNode;
2424 }

2428
2429float RenderLayerBacking::compositingOpacity(float rendererOpacity) const
2430{
2431 float finalOpacity = rendererOpacity;
2432
2433 for (auto* curr = m_owningLayer.parent(); curr; curr = curr->parent()) {
2434 // We only care about parents that are stacking contexts.
2435 // Recall that opacity creates stacking context.
2436 if (!curr->isCSSStackingContext())
2437 continue;
2438
2439 // If we found a compositing layer, we want to compute opacity
2440 // relative to it. So we can break here.
2441 if (curr->isComposited())
2442 break;
2443
2444 finalOpacity *= curr->renderer().opacity();
2445 }
2446
2447 return finalOpacity;
2448}

2456static bool canDirectlyCompositeBackgroundBackgroundImage(const RenderStyle& style)
2457{
2458 if (!GraphicsLayer::supportsContentsTiling())
2459 return false;
2460
2461 auto& fillLayer = style.backgroundLayers();
2462 if (fillLayer.next())
2463 return false;
2464
2465 if (!fillLayer.imagesAreLoaded())
2466 return false;
2467
2468 if (fillLayer.attachment() != FillAttachment::ScrollBackground)
2469 return false;
2470
2471 // FIXME: Allow color+image compositing when it makes sense.
2472 // For now bailing out.
2473 if (style.visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor).isVisible())
2474 return false;
2475
2476 // FIXME: support gradients with isGeneratedImage.
2477 auto* styleImage = fillLayer.image();
2478 if (!styleImage->hasCachedImage())
2479 return false;
2480
2481 auto* image = styleImage->cachedImage()->image();
2482 if (!image->isBitmapImage())
2483 return false;
2484
2485 return true;
2486}

2516void RenderLayerBacking::updateDirectlyCompositedBackgroundColor(PaintedContentsInfo& contentsInfo, bool& didUpdateContentsRect)
2517{
2518 if (m_backgroundLayer && !m_backgroundLayerPaintsFixedRootBackground && !contentsInfo.paintsBoxDecorations()) {
2519 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsToSolidColor(Color());
2520 m_backgroundLayer->setContentsToSolidColor(rendererBackgroundColor());
2521
2522 FloatRect contentsRect = backgroundBoxForSimpleContainerPainting();
2523 // NOTE: This is currently only used by RenderFullScreen, which we want to be
2524 // big enough to hide overflow areas of the root.
2525 contentsRect.inflate(contentsRect.size());

2537
2538 // An unset (invalid) color will remove the solid color.
2539 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsToSolidColor(backgroundColor);
2540 FloatRect contentsRect = backgroundBoxForSimpleContainerPainting();
2541 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsRect(contentsRect);
2542 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsClippingRect(FloatRoundedRect(contentsRect));

2552 return;

2597void RenderLayerBacking::updatePaintingPhases()
2598{
2599 // Phases for m_childClippingMaskLayer and m_maskLayer are set elsewhere.
2600 OptionSet<GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase> primaryLayerPhases = { GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Background, GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Foreground };
2601
2602 if (m_foregroundLayer) {
2603 OptionSet<GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase> foregroundLayerPhases { GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Foreground };
2604
2605 if (m_scrolledContentsLayer)
2606 foregroundLayerPhases.add(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::OverflowContents);
2607
2608 m_foregroundLayer->setPaintingPhase(foregroundLayerPhases);
2609 primaryLayerPhases.remove(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Foreground);
2610 }
2611
2612 if (m_backgroundLayer) {
2613 m_backgroundLayer->setPaintingPhase(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Background);
2614 primaryLayerPhases.remove(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Background);
2615 }
2616
2617 if (m_scrolledContentsLayer) {
2618 OptionSet<GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase> scrolledContentLayerPhases = { GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::OverflowContents, GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::CompositedScroll };
2619 if (!m_foregroundLayer)
2620 scrolledContentLayerPhases.add(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Foreground);
2621 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setPaintingPhase(scrolledContentLayerPhases);
2622
2623 primaryLayerPhases.remove(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Foreground);
2624 primaryLayerPhases.add(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::CompositedScroll);
2625 }
2626
2627 m_graphicsLayer->setPaintingPhase(primaryLayerPhases);
2628}

2630static bool supportsDirectlyCompositedBoxDecorations(const RenderLayerModelObject& renderer)
2631{
2632 if (!GraphicsLayer::supportsBackgroundColorContent())
2633 return false;
2634
2635 const RenderStyle& style = renderer.style();
2636 if (renderer.hasClip())
2637 return false;
2638
2639 if (hasPaintedBoxDecorationsOrBackgroundImage(style))
2640 return false;
2641
2642 // FIXME: We can't create a directly composited background if this
2643 // layer will have children that intersect with the background layer.
2644 // A better solution might be to introduce a flattening layer if
2645 // we do direct box decoration composition.
2646 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=119461
2647 if (hasPerspectiveOrPreserves3D(style))
2648 return false;
2649
2650 // FIXME: we should be able to allow backgroundComposite; However since this is not a common use case it has been deferred for now.
2651 if (style.backgroundComposite() != CompositeOperator::SourceOver)
2652 return false;
2653
2654 return true;
2655}

2665bool RenderLayerBacking::paintsContent(RenderLayer::PaintedContentRequest& request) const
2666{
2667 m_owningLayer.updateDescendantDependentFlags();
2668
2669 bool paintsContent = false;
2670
2671 if (m_owningLayer.hasVisibleContent() && m_owningLayer.hasNonEmptyChildRenderers(request))
2672 paintsContent = true;
2673
2674 if (request.isSatisfied())
2675 return paintsContent;
2676
2677 if (isPaintDestinationForDescendantLayers(request))
2678 paintsContent = true;
2679
2680 if (request.isSatisfied())
2681 return paintsContent;
2682
2683 if (request.hasPaintedContent == RequestState::Unknown)
2684 request.hasPaintedContent = RequestState::False;
2685
2686 if (request.hasSubpixelAntialiasedText == RequestState::Unknown)
2687 request.hasSubpixelAntialiasedText = RequestState::False;
2688
2689 return paintsContent;
2690}

2697// A "simple container layer" is a RenderLayer which has no visible content to render.
2698// It may have no children, or all its children may be themselves composited.
2699// This is a useful optimization, because it allows us to avoid allocating backing store.
2700bool RenderLayerBacking::isSimpleContainerCompositingLayer(PaintedContentsInfo& contentsInfo) const
2701{
2702 if (m_owningLayer.isRenderViewLayer())
2703 return false;
2704
2705 if (hasBackingSharingLayers())
2706 return false;
2707
2708 if (renderer().isRenderReplaced() && !isCompositedPlugin(renderer()))
2709 return false;
2710
2711 if (renderer().isTextControl())
2712 return false;
2713
2714 if (contentsInfo.paintsBoxDecorations() || contentsInfo.paintsContent())
2715 return false;
2716
2717 if (renderer().style().backgroundClip() == FillBox::Text)
2718 return false;
2719
2720 if (renderer().isDocumentElementRenderer() && m_owningLayer.isolatesCompositedBlending())
2721 return false;
2722
2723 return true;
2724}
2725
2726// Returning true stops the traversal.
2727enum class LayerTraversal { Continue, Stop };
2728
2729static LayerTraversal traverseVisibleNonCompositedDescendantLayers(RenderLayer& parent, const WTF::Function<LayerTraversal (const RenderLayer&)>& layerFunc)
2730{
2731 // FIXME: We shouldn't be called with a stale z-order lists. See bug 85512.
2732 parent.updateLayerListsIfNeeded();
2733
2734#if ASSERT_ENABLED
2735 LayerListMutationDetector mutationChecker(parent);
2736#endif
2737
2738 for (auto* childLayer : parent.normalFlowLayers()) {
2739 if (compositedWithOwnBackingStore(*childLayer))
2740 continue;
2741
2742 if (layerFunc(*childLayer) == LayerTraversal::Stop)
2743 return LayerTraversal::Stop;
2744
2745 if (traverseVisibleNonCompositedDescendantLayers(*childLayer, layerFunc) == LayerTraversal::Stop)
2746 return LayerTraversal::Stop;
2747 }
2748
2749 if (parent.isStackingContext() && !parent.hasVisibleDescendant())
2750 return LayerTraversal::Continue;
2751
2752 // Use the m_hasCompositingDescendant bit to optimize?
2753 for (auto* childLayer : parent.negativeZOrderLayers()) {
2754 if (compositedWithOwnBackingStore(*childLayer))
2755 continue;
2756
2757 if (layerFunc(*childLayer) == LayerTraversal::Stop)
2758 return LayerTraversal::Stop;
2759
2760 if (traverseVisibleNonCompositedDescendantLayers(*childLayer, layerFunc) == LayerTraversal::Stop)
2761 return LayerTraversal::Stop;
2762 }
2763
2764 for (auto* childLayer : parent.positiveZOrderLayers()) {
2765 if (compositedWithOwnBackingStore(*childLayer))
2766 continue;
2767
2768 if (layerFunc(*childLayer) == LayerTraversal::Stop)
2769 return LayerTraversal::Stop;
2770
2771 if (traverseVisibleNonCompositedDescendantLayers(*childLayer, layerFunc) == LayerTraversal::Stop)
2772 return LayerTraversal::Stop;
2773 }
2774
2775 return LayerTraversal::Continue;
2776}
2777
2778// Conservative test for having no rendered children.
2779bool RenderLayerBacking::isPaintDestinationForDescendantLayers(RenderLayer::PaintedContentRequest& request) const
2780{
2781 bool hasPaintingDescendant = false;
2782 traverseVisibleNonCompositedDescendantLayers(m_owningLayer, [&hasPaintingDescendant, &request](const RenderLayer& layer) {
2783 hasPaintingDescendant |= layer.isVisuallyNonEmpty(&request);
2784 return (hasPaintingDescendant && request.isSatisfied()) ? LayerTraversal::Stop : LayerTraversal::Continue;
2785 });
2786
2787 return hasPaintingDescendant;
2788}
2789
2790bool RenderLayerBacking::hasVisibleNonCompositedDescendants() const
2791{
2792 bool hasVisibleDescendant = false;
2793 traverseVisibleNonCompositedDescendantLayers(m_owningLayer, [&hasVisibleDescendant](const RenderLayer& layer) {
2794 hasVisibleDescendant |= layer.hasVisibleContent();
2795 return hasVisibleDescendant ? LayerTraversal::Stop : LayerTraversal::Continue;
2796 });
2797
2798 return hasVisibleDescendant;
2799}

2801bool RenderLayerBacking::containsPaintedContent(PaintedContentsInfo& contentsInfo) const
2802{
2803 if (contentsInfo.isSimpleContainer() || paintsIntoWindow() || paintsIntoCompositedAncestor() || m_artificiallyInflatedBounds || m_owningLayer.isReflection())
2804 return false;
2805
2806 if (contentsInfo.isDirectlyCompositedImage())
2807 return false;
2808
2809 // FIXME: we could optimize cases where the image, video or canvas is known to fill the border box entirely,
2810 // and set background color on the layer in that case, instead of allocating backing store and painting.
2811#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
2812 if (is<RenderVideo>(renderer()) && downcast<RenderVideo>(renderer()).shouldDisplayVideo())
2813 return m_owningLayer.hasVisibleBoxDecorationsOrBackground() || (!(downcast<RenderVideo>(renderer()).supportsAcceleratedRendering()) && m_requiresOwnBackingStore);
2814#endif
2815
2816#if ENABLE(WEBGL) || ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS)
2817 if (is<RenderHTMLCanvas>(renderer()) && canvasCompositingStrategy(renderer()) == CanvasAsLayerContents)
2818 return m_owningLayer.hasVisibleBoxDecorationsOrBackground();
2819#endif
2820
2821 return true;
2822}

2824// An image can be directly compositing if it's the sole content of the layer, and has no box decorations
2825// that require painting. Direct compositing saves backing store.
2826bool RenderLayerBacking::isDirectlyCompositedImage() const
2827{
2828 if (!is<RenderImage>(renderer()) || m_owningLayer.hasVisibleBoxDecorationsOrBackground() || m_owningLayer.paintsWithFilters() || renderer().hasClip())
2829 return false;
2830
2831#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
2832 if (is<RenderMedia>(renderer()))
2833 return false;
2834#endif
2835
2836 auto& imageRenderer = downcast<RenderImage>(renderer());
2837 if (auto* cachedImage = imageRenderer.cachedImage()) {
2838 if (!cachedImage->hasImage())
2839 return false;
2840
2841 auto* image = cachedImage->imageForRenderer(&imageRenderer);
2842 if (!is<BitmapImage>(image))
2843 return false;
2844
2845 if (downcast<BitmapImage>(*image).orientationForCurrentFrame() != ImageOrientation::None)
2846 return false;
2847
2848#if (PLATFORM(GTK) || PLATFORM(WPE))
2849 // GTK and WPE ports don't support rounded rect clipping at TextureMapper level, so they cannot
2850 // directly composite images that have border-radius propery. Draw them as non directly composited
2851 // content instead. See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=174157.
2852 if (imageRenderer.style().hasBorderRadius())
2853 return false;
2854#endif
2855
2856 return m_graphicsLayer->shouldDirectlyCompositeImage(image);
2857 }
2858
2859 return false;
2860}
2861
2862void RenderLayerBacking::contentChanged(ContentChangeType changeType)
2863{
2864 PaintedContentsInfo contentsInfo(*this);
2865 if ((changeType == ImageChanged) && contentsInfo.isDirectlyCompositedImage()) {
2866 updateImageContents(contentsInfo);
2867 return;
2868 }
2869
2870 if (changeType == VideoChanged) {
2871 compositor().scheduleCompositingLayerUpdate();
2872 return;
2873 }
2874
2875#if ENABLE(MODEL_ELEMENT)
2876 if (changeType == ModelChanged) {
2877 compositor().scheduleCompositingLayerUpdate();
2878 return;
2879 }
2880#endif
2881
2882 if ((changeType == BackgroundImageChanged) && canDirectlyCompositeBackgroundBackgroundImage(renderer().style()))
2883 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingConfigurationUpdate();
2884
2885 if ((changeType == MaskImageChanged) && m_maskLayer)
2886 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingConfigurationUpdate();
2887
2888#if ENABLE(WEBGL) || ENABLE(WEBGPU) || ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS)
2889 if ((changeType == CanvasChanged || changeType == CanvasPixelsChanged) && renderer().isCanvas() && canvasCompositingStrategy(renderer()) == CanvasAsLayerContents) {
2890 if (changeType == CanvasChanged)
2891 compositor().scheduleCompositingLayerUpdate();
2892
2893 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsNeedsDisplay();
2894 return;
2895 }
2896#endif
2897}
2898
2899void RenderLayerBacking::updateImageContents(PaintedContentsInfo& contentsInfo)
2900{
2901 auto& imageRenderer = downcast<RenderImage>(renderer());
2902
2903 auto* cachedImage = imageRenderer.cachedImage();
2904 if (!cachedImage)
2905 return;
2906
2907 auto* image = cachedImage->imageForRenderer(&imageRenderer);
2908 if (!image)
2909 return;
2910
2911 // We have to wait until the image is fully loaded before setting it on the layer.
2912 if (!cachedImage->isLoaded())
2913 return;
2914
2915 updateContentsRects();
2916 m_graphicsLayer->setContentsToImage(image);
2917
2918 updateDrawsContent(contentsInfo);
2919
2920 // Image animation is "lazy", in that it automatically stops unless someone is drawing
2921 // the image. So we have to kick the animation each time; this has the downside that the
2922 // image will keep animating, even if its layer is not visible.
2923 image->startAnimation();
2924}

2932 origin.setZ(style.transformOriginZ());

2999

3058void RenderLayerBacking::setContentsNeedDisplay(GraphicsLayer::ShouldClipToLayer shouldClip)
3059{
3060 ASSERT(!paintsIntoCompositedAncestor());
3061
3062 // Use the repaint as a trigger to re-evaluate direct compositing (which is never used on the root layer).
3063 if (!m_owningLayer.isRenderViewLayer())
3064 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingConfigurationUpdate();
3065
3066 m_owningLayer.invalidateEventRegion(RenderLayer::EventRegionInvalidationReason::Paint);
3067
3068 auto& frameView = renderer().view().frameView();
3069 if (m_isMainFrameRenderViewLayer && frameView.isTrackingRepaints())
3070 frameView.addTrackedRepaintRect(owningLayer().absoluteBoundingBoxForPainting());
3071
3072 if (m_graphicsLayer && m_graphicsLayer->drawsContent()) {
3073 // By default, setNeedsDisplay will clip to the size of the GraphicsLayer, which does not include margin tiles.
3074 // So if the TiledBacking has a margin that needs to be invalidated, we need to send in a rect to setNeedsDisplayInRect
3075 // that is large enough to include the margin. TiledBacking::bounds() includes the margin.
3076 auto* tiledBacking = this->tiledBacking();
3077 FloatRect rectToRepaint = tiledBacking ? tiledBacking->bounds() : FloatRect(FloatPoint(0, 0), m_graphicsLayer->size());
3078 m_graphicsLayer->setNeedsDisplayInRect(rectToRepaint, shouldClip);
3079 }
3080
3081 if (m_foregroundLayer && m_foregroundLayer->drawsContent())
3082 m_foregroundLayer->setNeedsDisplay();
3083
3084 if (m_backgroundLayer && m_backgroundLayer->drawsContent())
3085 m_backgroundLayer->setNeedsDisplay();
3086
3087 if (m_maskLayer && m_maskLayer->drawsContent())
3088 m_maskLayer->setNeedsDisplay();
3089
3090 if (m_childClippingMaskLayer && m_childClippingMaskLayer->drawsContent())
3091 m_childClippingMaskLayer->setNeedsDisplay();
3092
3093 if (m_scrolledContentsLayer && m_scrolledContentsLayer->drawsContent())
3094 m_scrolledContentsLayer->setNeedsDisplay();
3095}

3200
3201 if (!eventRegionContext) {

3205 InspectorInstrumentation::didPaint(layer.renderer(), paintDirtyRect);

3239OptionSet<RenderLayer::PaintLayerFlag> RenderLayerBacking::paintFlagsForLayer(const GraphicsLayer& graphicsLayer) const
3240{

3244 if (paintingPhase.contains(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Background))

3246 if (paintingPhase.contains(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Foreground))
3247 paintFlags.add(RenderLayer::PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingForegroundPhase);
3248 if (paintingPhase.contains(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::Mask))
3249 paintFlags.add(RenderLayer::PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingMaskPhase);
3250 if (paintingPhase.contains(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::ClipPath))
3251 paintFlags.add(RenderLayer::PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingClipPathPhase);

3254 if (paintingPhase.contains(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::OverflowContents))

3256 if (paintingPhase.contains(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::CompositedScroll))
3257 paintFlags.add(RenderLayer::PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingScrollingPhase);
3258
3259 if (&graphicsLayer == m_backgroundLayer.get() && m_backgroundLayerPaintsFixedRootBackground)
3260 paintFlags.add({ RenderLayer::PaintLayerFlag::PaintingRootBackgroundOnly, RenderLayer::PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingForegroundPhase }); // Need PaintLayerFlag::PaintingCompositingForegroundPhase to walk child layers.
3261 else if (compositor().fixedRootBackgroundLayer())
3262 paintFlags.add(RenderLayer::PaintLayerFlag::PaintingSkipRootBackground);

3437// Up-call from compositing layer drawing callback.
3438void RenderLayerBacking::paintContents(const GraphicsLayer* graphicsLayer, GraphicsContext& context, const FloatRect& clip, GraphicsLayerPaintBehavior layerPaintBehavior)
3439{
3440#ifndef NDEBUG
3441 renderer().page().setIsPainting(true);
3442#endif
3443
3444#if PLATFORM(MAC)
3445 LocalDefaultSystemAppearance localAppearance(renderer().useDarkAppearance());
3446#endif
3447
3448 // The dirtyRect is in the coords of the painting root.
3449 FloatRect adjustedClipRect = clip;
3450 adjustedClipRect.move(m_subpixelOffsetFromRenderer);
3451 IntRect dirtyRect = enclosingIntRect(adjustedClipRect);
3452
3453 if (!graphicsLayer->repaintCount())
3454 layerPaintBehavior |= GraphicsLayerPaintFirstTilePaint;
3455
3456 if (graphicsLayer == m_graphicsLayer.get()
3457 || graphicsLayer == m_foregroundLayer.get()
3458 || graphicsLayer == m_backgroundLayer.get()
3459 || graphicsLayer == m_maskLayer.get()
3460 || graphicsLayer == m_childClippingMaskLayer.get()
3461 || graphicsLayer == m_scrolledContentsLayer.get()) {
3462
3463 if (!graphicsLayer->paintingPhase().contains(GraphicsLayerPaintingPhase::OverflowContents))
3464 dirtyRect.intersect(enclosingIntRect(compositedBoundsIncludingMargin()));
3465
3466 // We have to use the same root as for hit testing, because both methods can compute and cache clipRects.
3467 OptionSet<PaintBehavior> behavior = PaintBehavior::Normal;
3468 if (layerPaintBehavior == GraphicsLayerPaintSnapshotting)
3469 behavior.add(PaintBehavior::Snapshotting);
3470
3471 if (layerPaintBehavior == GraphicsLayerPaintFirstTilePaint)
3472 behavior.add(PaintBehavior::TileFirstPaint);
3473
3474 paintIntoLayer(graphicsLayer, context, dirtyRect, behavior);
3475
3476 auto visibleDebugOverlayRegions = OptionSet<DebugOverlayRegions>::fromRaw(renderer().settings().visibleDebugOverlayRegions());
3477 if (visibleDebugOverlayRegions.containsAny({ DebugOverlayRegions::TouchActionRegion, DebugOverlayRegions::EditableElementRegion, DebugOverlayRegions::WheelEventHandlerRegion }))
3478 paintDebugOverlays(graphicsLayer, context);
3479
3480 } else if (graphicsLayer == layerForHorizontalScrollbar()) {
3481 if (m_owningLayer.hasVisibleContent()) {
3482 auto* scrollableArea = m_owningLayer.scrollableArea();
3483 ASSERT(scrollableArea);
3484
3485 paintScrollbar(scrollableArea->horizontalScrollbar(), context, dirtyRect);
3486 }
3487 } else if (graphicsLayer == layerForVerticalScrollbar()) {
3488 if (m_owningLayer.hasVisibleContent()) {
3489 auto* scrollableArea = m_owningLayer.scrollableArea();
3490 ASSERT(scrollableArea);
3491
3492 paintScrollbar(scrollableArea->verticalScrollbar(), context, dirtyRect);
3493 }
3494 } else if (graphicsLayer == layerForScrollCorner()) {
3495 auto* scrollableArea = m_owningLayer.scrollableArea();
3496 ASSERT(scrollableArea);
3497
3498 auto cornerRect = scrollableArea->overflowControlsRects().scrollCornerOrResizerRect();
3499 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
3500 context.translate(-cornerRect.location());
3501 LayoutRect transformedClip = LayoutRect(clip);
3502 transformedClip.moveBy(cornerRect.location());
3503 scrollableArea->paintScrollCorner(context, IntPoint(), snappedIntRect(transformedClip));
3504 scrollableArea->paintResizer(context, IntPoint(), transformedClip);

3568bool RenderLayerBacking::shouldDumpPropertyForLayer(const GraphicsLayer* layer, const char* propertyName, LayerTreeAsTextBehavior flags) const
3569{
3570 // For backwards compatibility with WebKit1 and other platforms,
3571 // skip some properties on the root tile cache.
3572 if (m_isMainFrameRenderViewLayer && layer == m_graphicsLayer.get() && !(flags & LayerTreeAsTextIncludeRootLayerProperties)) {
3573 if (!strcmp(propertyName, "drawsContent"))
3574 return false;
3575
3576 // Background color could be of interest to tests or other dumpers if it's non-white.
3577 if (!strcmp(propertyName, "backgroundColor") && Color::isWhiteColor(layer->backgroundColor()))
3578 return false;
3579
3580 // The root tile cache's repaints will show up at the top with FrameView's,
3581 // so don't dump them twice.
3582 if (!strcmp(propertyName, "repaintRects"))
3583 return false;
3584 }
3585
3586 return true;
3587}

3622bool RenderLayerBacking::startAnimation(double timeOffset, const Animation& animation, const KeyframeList& keyframes)
3623{
3624 bool hasOpacity = keyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyOpacity);
3625 bool hasRotate = renderer().isBox() && keyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyRotate);
3626 bool hasScale = renderer().isBox() && keyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyScale);
3627 bool hasTranslate = renderer().isBox() && keyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyTranslate);
3628 bool hasTransform = renderer().isBox() && keyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyTransform);
3629 bool hasFilter = keyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyFilter);
3630
3631 bool hasBackdropFilter = false;
3632#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
3633 hasBackdropFilter = keyframes.containsProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter);
3634#endif
3635
3636 if (!hasOpacity && !hasRotate && !hasScale && !hasTranslate && !hasTransform && !hasFilter && !hasBackdropFilter)
3637 return false;
3638
3639 KeyframeValueList rotateVector(AnimatedPropertyRotate);
3640 KeyframeValueList scaleVector(AnimatedPropertyScale);
3641 KeyframeValueList translateVector(AnimatedPropertyTranslate);
3642 KeyframeValueList transformVector(AnimatedPropertyTransform);
3643 KeyframeValueList opacityVector(AnimatedPropertyOpacity);
3644 KeyframeValueList filterVector(AnimatedPropertyFilter);
3645#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
3646 KeyframeValueList backdropFilterVector(AnimatedPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter);
3647#endif
3648
3649 size_t numKeyframes = keyframes.size();
3650 for (size_t i = 0; i < numKeyframes; ++i) {
3651 const KeyframeValue& currentKeyframe = keyframes[i];
3652 const RenderStyle* keyframeStyle = currentKeyframe.style();
3653 double key = currentKeyframe.key();
3654
3655 if (!keyframeStyle)
3656 continue;
3657
3658 auto* tf = currentKeyframe.timingFunction();
3659
3660 bool isFirstOrLastKeyframe = key == 0 || key == 1;
3661 if ((hasRotate && isFirstOrLastKeyframe) || currentKeyframe.containsProperty(CSSPropertyRotate))
3662 rotateVector.insert(makeUnique<TransformAnimationValue>(key, keyframeStyle->rotate(), tf));
3663
3664 if ((hasScale && isFirstOrLastKeyframe) || currentKeyframe.containsProperty(CSSPropertyScale))
3665 scaleVector.insert(makeUnique<TransformAnimationValue>(key, keyframeStyle->scale(), tf));
3666
3667 if ((hasTranslate && isFirstOrLastKeyframe) || currentKeyframe.containsProperty(CSSPropertyTranslate))
3668 translateVector.insert(makeUnique<TransformAnimationValue>(key, keyframeStyle->translate(), tf));
3669
3670 if ((hasTransform && isFirstOrLastKeyframe) || currentKeyframe.containsProperty(CSSPropertyTransform))
3671 transformVector.insert(makeUnique<TransformAnimationValue>(key, keyframeStyle->transform(), tf));
3672
3673 if ((hasOpacity && isFirstOrLastKeyframe) || currentKeyframe.containsProperty(CSSPropertyOpacity))
3674 opacityVector.insert(makeUnique<FloatAnimationValue>(key, keyframeStyle->opacity(), tf));
3675
3676 if ((hasFilter && isFirstOrLastKeyframe) || currentKeyframe.containsProperty(CSSPropertyFilter))
3677 filterVector.insert(makeUnique<FilterAnimationValue>(key, keyframeStyle->filter(), tf));
3678
3679#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
3680 if ((hasBackdropFilter && isFirstOrLastKeyframe) || currentKeyframe.containsProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter))
3681 backdropFilterVector.insert(makeUnique<FilterAnimationValue>(key, keyframeStyle->backdropFilter(), tf));
3682#endif
3683 }
3684
3685 if (!renderer().settings().acceleratedCompositedAnimationsEnabled())
3686 return false;
3687
3688 bool didAnimate = false;
3689
3690 if (hasRotate && m_graphicsLayer->addAnimation(rotateVector, snappedIntRect(renderBox()->borderBoxRect()).size(), &animation, keyframes.animationName(), timeOffset))
3691 didAnimate = true;
3692
3693 if (hasScale && m_graphicsLayer->addAnimation(scaleVector, snappedIntRect(renderBox()->borderBoxRect()).size(), &animation, keyframes.animationName(), timeOffset))
3694 didAnimate = true;
3695
3696 if (hasTranslate && m_graphicsLayer->addAnimation(translateVector, snappedIntRect(renderBox()->borderBoxRect()).size(), &animation, keyframes.animationName(), timeOffset))
3697 didAnimate = true;
3698
3699 if (hasTransform && m_graphicsLayer->addAnimation(transformVector, snappedIntRect(renderBox()->borderBoxRect()).size(), &animation, keyframes.animationName(), timeOffset))
3700 didAnimate = true;
3701
3702 if (hasOpacity && m_graphicsLayer->addAnimation(opacityVector, IntSize { }, &animation, keyframes.animationName(), timeOffset))
3703 didAnimate = true;
3704
3705 if (hasFilter && m_graphicsLayer->addAnimation(filterVector, IntSize { }, &animation, keyframes.animationName(), timeOffset))
3706 didAnimate = true;
3707
3708#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
3709 if (hasBackdropFilter && m_graphicsLayer->addAnimation(backdropFilterVector, IntSize { }, &animation, keyframes.animationName(), timeOffset))
3710 didAnimate = true;
3711#endif
3712
3713 if (didAnimate) {
3714 m_owningLayer.setNeedsPostLayoutCompositingUpdate();
3715 m_owningLayer.setNeedsCompositingGeometryUpdate();
3716 }
3717
3718 return didAnimate;
3719}

3780LayoutRect RenderLayerBacking::compositedBoundsIncludingMargin() const
3781{
3782 auto* tiledBacking = this->tiledBacking();
3783 if (!tiledBacking || !tiledBacking->hasMargins())
3784 return compositedBounds();
3785
3786 LayoutRect boundsIncludingMargin = compositedBounds();
3787 LayoutUnit leftMarginWidth = tiledBacking->leftMarginWidth();
3788 LayoutUnit topMarginHeight = tiledBacking->topMarginHeight();
3789
3790 boundsIncludingMargin.moveBy(LayoutPoint(-leftMarginWidth, -topMarginHeight));
3791 boundsIncludingMargin.expand(leftMarginWidth + tiledBacking->rightMarginWidth(), topMarginHeight + tiledBacking->bottomMarginHeight());
3792
3793 return boundsIncludingMargin;
3794}

3928TransformationMatrix RenderLayerBacking::transformMatrixForProperty(AnimatedPropertyID property) const
3929{
3930 auto* box = renderBox();
3931 if (!box)
3932 return { };
3933
3934 TransformationMatrix matrix;
3935
3936 auto applyTransformOperation = [&](TransformOperation* operation) {
3937 if (operation)
3938 operation->apply(matrix, snappedIntRect(renderBox()->borderBoxRect()).size());
3939 };
3940
3941 if (property == AnimatedPropertyTranslate)
3942 applyTransformOperation(renderer().style().translate());
3943 else if (property == AnimatedPropertyScale)
3944 applyTransformOperation(renderer().style().scale());
3945 else if (property == AnimatedPropertyRotate)
3946 applyTransformOperation(renderer().style().rotate());
3947 else if (property == AnimatedPropertyTransform)
3948 renderer().style().transform().apply(snappedIntRect(renderBox()->borderBoxRect()).size(), matrix);
3949 else
3950 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3951
3952 return matrix;
3953}
